1
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,250
[birds chirping]

2
00:00:58,333 --> 00:01:01,333
[solemn music rises]

3
00:01:01,917 --> 00:01:03,792
[braying]

4
00:01:09,125 --> 00:01:10,667
[braying loudly]

5
00:01:10,750 --> 00:01:11,792
[gasps]

6
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:16,333
[snorting, huffing]

7
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:23,167
[coins rattling]

8
00:01:25,667 --> 00:01:27,000
It's the Musso farm.

9
00:01:27,083 --> 00:01:29,000
Bella's not well. Yes. Please hurry!

10
00:01:32,250 --> 00:01:34,250
[braying continues]

11
00:01:36,833 --> 00:01:39,500
[light upbeat music playing]

12
00:01:41,542 --> 00:01:43,417
It's a good thing you heard her braying.

13
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:46,625
If you hadn't called when you did,
they probably would've died.

14
00:01:47,292 --> 00:01:48,667
It was a breech birth.

15
00:01:52,042 --> 00:01:54,250
How many times a day
do we give the antibiotic?

16
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,375
- I'll write it all down.
- Thank you, Doctor.

17
00:02:00,708 --> 00:02:03,208
Hello… Have you thought of a name?

18
00:02:03,292 --> 00:02:04,875
[in Sign Language] Topsy-Turvy.

19
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:07,375
"Topsy-Turvy?"
What, are you trying to be funny?

20
00:02:07,458 --> 00:02:09,750
I told you yesterday
Bella felt like she had a fever.

21
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:11,917
But you don't listen to me.
You're so hard-headed.

22
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,167
We're both hard-headed.

23
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:17,083
So glad we moved here
to become mule breeders.

24
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,083
[music fades]

25
00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:35,125
[faint music in headphones]

26
00:02:35,208 --> 00:02:40,250
It's your first day at school,
and that's what you're wearing? Go change!

27
00:02:41,917 --> 00:02:44,458
Mama! Mama! Don't be a pain!

28
00:02:46,792 --> 00:02:48,333
To Topsy-Turvy!

29
00:02:49,583 --> 00:02:51,167
- [clinking]
- [sighs]

30
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:53,833
[water running]

31
00:02:57,042 --> 00:02:58,042
[sighs]

32
00:02:58,125 --> 00:02:59,833
[sloshing]

33
00:02:59,917 --> 00:03:00,917
[clattering]

34
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,292
[spoon clanking]

35
00:03:02,375 --> 00:03:03,292
[whisking]

36
00:03:03,375 --> 00:03:04,792
- [bells clink]
- [saw buzzes]

37
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:06,083
[swishing loudly]

38
00:03:06,167 --> 00:03:08,833
[scattered clamor continues]

39
00:03:08,917 --> 00:03:09,917
[clinking]

40
00:03:09,958 --> 00:03:11,167
- [slurps]
- [slams]

41
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:12,333
[burps loudly]

42
00:03:12,417 --> 00:03:13,667
What the hell, guys?!

43
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:16,250
Try making an effort?

44
00:03:17,792 --> 00:03:20,333
[loud clanking, banging]

45
00:03:21,708 --> 00:03:22,958
- [notes pinging]
- Boo!

46
00:03:27,042 --> 00:03:29,333
No music when we're at the table!

47
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:34,958
See ya! I'm leaving. Gonna be late.

48
00:03:35,042 --> 00:03:36,042
See ya, bitch.

49
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:39,000
Right back at you!

50
00:03:41,792 --> 00:03:44,083
Mama, please! I'm not 4 anymore.

51
00:03:44,167 --> 00:03:46,000
I'll see you at the clinic. Bye-bye!

52
00:03:48,542 --> 00:03:49,542
[sighs]

53
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:51,167
[chickens clucking in distance]

54
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:54,708
["Dal giorno in cui sei NATO tu"
by Andrea Laszlo De Simone plays]

55
00:03:54,792 --> 00:03:56,792
[song playing in headphones]

56
00:04:12,042 --> 00:04:15,667
FEEL MY VOICE

57
00:05:05,542 --> 00:05:08,292
[sings in Italian]
♪ <i>…the most beautiful in the world </i> ♪

58
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:12,042
♪ <i>And your eyes are the most sincere </i> ♪

59
00:05:13,167 --> 00:05:17,250
♪ <i>And in my heart lies a true love </i> ♪

60
00:05:18,042 --> 00:05:23,292
♪ <i>Since the day you were born </i> ♪

61
00:05:23,875 --> 00:05:25,708
[ringtone playing]

62
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:28,958
[in English] Yes, Mrs. Bocchio?

63
00:05:29,042 --> 00:05:31,522
- [indistinct chatter]
- [girl] I hear we're having a quiz today!

64
00:05:31,583 --> 00:05:34,417
Yes, I'm afraid we have to
cancel the order, Mr. Bocchio.

65
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,417
A 20% increase is just too much.

66
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:39,542
Our donkeys will never notice
the difference between your feed

67
00:05:39,625 --> 00:05:41,333
and Mr. Marzarin's, I assure you.

68
00:05:41,417 --> 00:05:43,417
Unless you're willing to meet us halfway?

69
00:05:44,375 --> 00:05:46,625
We appreciate that.
All the best to your wife.

70
00:05:46,708 --> 00:05:48,833
[school bell ringing]

71
00:05:48,917 --> 00:05:52,750
We can't move towards something
unless we know where we came from.

72
00:05:53,292 --> 00:05:57,792
Now, these tests are designed to help us
assess where each of you stands

73
00:05:57,875 --> 00:06:00,125
before you begin these last three years.

74
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:04,917
[class laughing]

75
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:08,667
[teacher] I assess that
this young lady is still in dreamland.

76
00:06:09,208 --> 00:06:11,000
- Am I right?
- Yes.

77
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,375
[teacher] Well,
aren't we off to a good start…

78
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:18,333
So, what will our educational goals be
for these next three years?

79
00:06:18,417 --> 00:06:21,292
One… to deepen our self-knowledge.

80
00:06:22,125 --> 00:06:24,625
Two… to strengthen
our confidence in our abilities.

81
00:06:24,708 --> 00:06:26,542
- How are ya? Martina.
- And three…

82
00:06:26,625 --> 00:06:28,875
- To learn to face our mistakes.
- Eletta.

83
00:06:28,958 --> 00:06:30,083
Eletta?

84
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:32,125
Really?

85
00:06:32,208 --> 00:06:35,208
[soft pop song playing]

86
00:06:35,292 --> 00:06:37,083
That's Gregorio. [Chuckles]

87
00:06:37,167 --> 00:06:39,333
He's totally obsessed with me.

88
00:06:39,417 --> 00:06:41,625
First, I gave him a little kiss
in grade school,

89
00:06:41,708 --> 00:06:43,500
then we made out more in middle school,

90
00:06:43,583 --> 00:06:45,833
and finally, I let him
explore a bit up top.

91
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,000
[laughs] I blame it all on my parents.
They're both shrinks.

92
00:06:51,083 --> 00:06:53,250
They told me I needed
to work on my empathy.

93
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:55,625
So, that's what I did. And your parents?

94
00:06:55,708 --> 00:06:57,167
They're donkey breeders.

95
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,375
Tell me you're joking.

96
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:02,333
- Eletta, who breeds donkeys?
- We do, on our farm.

97
00:07:04,542 --> 00:07:05,833
Tell me more…

98
00:07:05,917 --> 00:07:08,542
Besides the donkeys we have geese,
some sheep and chickens.

99
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:11,958
No, I mean do you have any other
weird stuff to tell me about yourself?

100
00:07:12,042 --> 00:07:13,750
Nope. Nothing else "weird."

101
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:15,958
So! What's left to choose from?

102
00:07:16,042 --> 00:07:19,375
Ceramics, photography, singing, theater…

103
00:07:19,458 --> 00:07:20,917
Do you think, "Singing?"

104
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,333
Shit, no. I'm tone-deaf.

105
00:07:22,417 --> 00:07:23,667
[music fades]

106
00:07:28,167 --> 00:07:29,500
[Eletta] You know him?

107
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:32,708
A douche bag from fifth year.
Nickname's "Marco the Giant."

108
00:07:32,792 --> 00:07:34,417
A fighter in the MMA.

109
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,500
You know it?

110
00:07:35,583 --> 00:07:36,833
[soft pop music resumes]

111
00:07:36,917 --> 00:07:38,500
[yelling]

112
00:07:43,458 --> 00:07:46,333
[friend] Look at that.
Naked men beating each other up!

113
00:07:46,417 --> 00:07:48,417
- [chuckles]
- Let's pick this course.

114
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,792
- Hi.
- Name?

115
00:07:49,875 --> 00:07:51,458
Marco… Traversato.

116
00:07:52,208 --> 00:07:53,958
- [woman] Course pick?
- Singing.

117
00:07:54,042 --> 00:07:56,667
- Singing…
- Maybe not as tough as he seems to be.

118
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:57,750
Really?

119
00:07:58,292 --> 00:07:59,875
Eletta Musso. Singing.

120
00:07:59,958 --> 00:08:01,333
[man] Alright. Sign here, please.

121
00:08:01,417 --> 00:08:03,542
- Do you know what you're doing?
- [chuckles]

122
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:08,208
- Singing. [Sighs]
- [man] Um, name, please?

123
00:08:08,792 --> 00:08:10,333
- Whose?
- [man] Uh, yours?

124
00:08:10,417 --> 00:08:11,500
Martina.

125
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:13,875
- Tell me the course.
- Put your hands down, dumb-dumb.

126
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,542
[laughs] He'll take Singing, please.

127
00:08:17,042 --> 00:08:18,167
[laughs]

128
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:21,833
<i>♪ Outside my quiet rooms… ♪</i>

129
00:08:26,083 --> 00:08:28,917
- That blonde bitch wants The Giant.
- Stop it! [Chuckles]

130
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,583
[cheering]

131
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:33,917
[sighs]

132
00:08:35,625 --> 00:08:38,000
[heavy metal blasting over speakers]

133
00:08:43,625 --> 00:08:44,833
What are you doing?!

134
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,583
Dad! Dad! Go, go!

135
00:08:50,667 --> 00:08:52,167
C'mon, Dad! Stop. Get in!

136
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:57,667
- [music stops]
- [booing]

137
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:59,958
We're supposed to meet
at the doctor's, not here!

138
00:09:00,042 --> 00:09:01,125
- [booing]
- Mama, drive!

139
00:09:01,208 --> 00:09:03,309
Wanted to do you a favor.
You didn't sleep last night.

140
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:04,973
[Eletta] You had the music at full blast!

141
00:09:06,042 --> 00:09:08,583
Mom, drive! Mom, drive! Drive!

142
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:12,292
- [horn blaring]
- Mom, drive!

143
00:09:12,375 --> 00:09:13,833
Drive, damn it! Hurry!

144
00:09:13,917 --> 00:09:15,583
[blaring horn fades]

145
00:09:19,542 --> 00:09:21,958
So it's the same results as the last time.

146
00:09:22,042 --> 00:09:23,958
There's no improvement at all.

147
00:09:24,583 --> 00:09:26,000
Are they applying the cream?

148
00:09:26,083 --> 00:09:27,667
Are you applying the cream?

149
00:09:29,083 --> 00:09:31,625
Yes. I rub the cream
into my vagina every night.

150
00:09:31,708 --> 00:09:34,083
Yet somehow your mother's mycosis
has gotten worse.

151
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:38,292
But your father is applying the cream
I prescribed for him too, right?

152
00:09:38,375 --> 00:09:40,208
Papa, are you applying the cream?

153
00:09:42,792 --> 00:09:44,125
Are you using the cream?!

154
00:09:45,292 --> 00:09:48,292
I used to, but not anymore.
It really greases up…

155
00:09:48,375 --> 00:09:49,750
It greases up my underwear.

156
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:53,375
And the donkeys like it.

157
00:09:55,208 --> 00:10:00,750
The other day,
Osvaldo tried to nip my balls.

158
00:10:05,125 --> 00:10:06,375
[blows raspberry]

159
00:10:06,458 --> 00:10:07,458
That's enough!

160
00:10:10,167 --> 00:10:11,708
Excuse them.

161
00:10:11,792 --> 00:10:15,167
Your father has to apply the cream.
Otherwise, it simply won't work.

162
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:17,958
Papa, you have to apply the cream!
It's important!

163
00:10:18,042 --> 00:10:19,708
And no more sexual intercourse.

164
00:10:19,792 --> 00:10:21,000
And sex must stop.

165
00:10:21,083 --> 00:10:22,250
For how long?

166
00:10:22,333 --> 00:10:23,542
Three weeks minimum.

167
00:10:24,375 --> 00:10:25,583
Mama!

168
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:27,000
Forget it!

169
00:10:27,083 --> 00:10:28,458
Mama!

170
00:10:28,542 --> 00:10:31,417
Mama, what do you mean
you don't agree with the treatment?

171
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:32,875
You suddenly a doctor?

172
00:10:32,958 --> 00:10:34,125
You've got to listen!

173
00:10:34,208 --> 00:10:35,583
I am so sorry, Doctor.

174
00:10:36,208 --> 00:10:38,583
- [indistinct chatter]
- [piano tune playing]

175
00:10:38,667 --> 00:10:41,292
[girl] I took the bus this morning.
It was god-awful!

176
00:10:45,042 --> 00:10:47,208
I didn't want to do this.
My mother made me.

177
00:10:49,167 --> 00:10:50,583
If he's worth a shot…

178
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,542
- Then you gotta take it.
- No, no! Please!

179
00:10:55,625 --> 00:10:56,917
[professor] Good morning!

180
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:58,833
[students] Good morning!

181
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:03,167
I am Professor Giuliana Palumbo.

182
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:06,458
First off, thank you for wanting
to take my singing course,

183
00:11:06,542 --> 00:11:08,125
but there are too many of you.

184
00:11:08,208 --> 00:11:10,250
I'm gonna have to weed some of you out.

185
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:11,917
You! Come over here.

186
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,042
Name?

187
00:11:13,125 --> 00:11:14,333
- Elena.
- Ah.

188
00:11:15,125 --> 00:11:17,375
- [chord playing]
- Say it again but sing it.

189
00:11:17,458 --> 00:11:20,167
<i>♪ Elena-ah-ha-ah-haa ♪</i>

190
00:11:20,792 --> 00:11:22,875
Soprano. Great. Go over there.

191
00:11:24,292 --> 00:11:27,083
<i>♪ Luuu-caaaa ♪</i>

192
00:11:27,167 --> 00:11:28,833
A beautiful bass.

193
00:11:28,917 --> 00:11:30,667
Men can stand over there. Very good.

194
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:33,958
You. Tall one.

195
00:11:36,667 --> 00:11:37,500
Marco.

196
00:11:37,583 --> 00:11:39,583
[piano plays notes]

197
00:11:40,208 --> 00:11:42,125
<i>♪ Marco ♪</i>

198
00:11:43,417 --> 00:11:44,458
Why are you shy?

199
00:11:45,792 --> 00:11:47,667
Why? Again. Sing it.

200
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,167
[piano plays notes]

201
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:53,208
[fuller] <i>♪ Marco ♪</i>

202
00:11:54,708 --> 00:11:56,833
Much better.
Stand over there with the others.

203
00:11:56,917 --> 00:11:59,125
[ambient melancholy music rises]

204
00:11:59,208 --> 00:12:00,375
You. You're next.

205
00:12:03,667 --> 00:12:05,333
♪ <i>Enrico </i> ♪

206
00:12:05,417 --> 00:12:06,500
♪ <i>Federica </i> ♪

207
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:08,083
Better? [Laughs]

208
00:12:08,167 --> 00:12:10,167
[airy vocalizations lilting]

209
00:12:10,250 --> 00:12:12,833
[off-key] <i>♪ Senna ♪</i>

210
00:12:13,583 --> 00:12:15,292
Oh my God, this is difficult.

211
00:12:16,042 --> 00:12:16,958
♪ <i>Lorenzo </i> ♪

212
00:12:17,042 --> 00:12:19,083
[chuckling quietly]

213
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,333
Do you find something funny?

214
00:12:24,125 --> 00:12:26,750
Uh, you there. Laughing Girl.
C'mere and sing for me.

215
00:12:26,833 --> 00:12:28,292
[ambient music fades]

216
00:12:28,375 --> 00:12:29,667
<i>♪ Martina… ♪</i>

217
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:32,250
No. Martina, no. Thank you for your time.

218
00:12:32,333 --> 00:12:34,667
- But you didn't let me finish!
- Uh, it's better this way.

219
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:36,292
I'm sure that you have other talents.

220
00:12:36,375 --> 00:12:39,417
- Believe me, I have many. See you, Eletta.
- Uh, yeah… I have no doubt.

221
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:41,417
No. Where are you going? One second.

222
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:44,625
- [Eletta] I'm leaving. Thanks.
- No, I haven't heard you sing. C'mere.

223
00:12:44,708 --> 00:12:46,042
Come on back here.

224
00:12:46,125 --> 00:12:47,208
Go on, Eletta.

225
00:12:52,792 --> 00:12:54,875
[chord sounds on piano]

226
00:12:54,958 --> 00:12:56,708
<i>♪ Eletta ♪</i>

227
00:13:00,167 --> 00:13:01,667
Well, you-you can sing, but…

228
00:13:02,542 --> 00:13:04,958
You can sing even better than that.
Don't be shy.

229
00:13:05,042 --> 00:13:06,333
Try one more time, okay?

230
00:13:10,458 --> 00:13:12,958
<i>♪ Eh-letta ♪</i>

231
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,583
Another soprano.

232
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,458
You should stay.

233
00:13:21,542 --> 00:13:22,458
Please.

234
00:13:22,542 --> 00:13:23,542
Thank you.

235
00:13:26,792 --> 00:13:30,042
<i>♪ Gem ♪</i>

236
00:13:30,125 --> 00:13:33,000
The passion is there, for sure.
But, I'm sorry, you didn't make it.

237
00:13:33,083 --> 00:13:34,708
[laughs]

238
00:13:34,792 --> 00:13:36,625
You're going too fast! Too fast!

239
00:13:36,708 --> 00:13:38,542
Oh! Whoa!

240
00:13:38,625 --> 00:13:40,000
[laughing]

241
00:13:43,375 --> 00:13:44,500
What did I say?!

242
00:13:47,167 --> 00:13:50,000
- [Martina] What are these?
- [Eletta] They're the Giseldes.

243
00:13:50,083 --> 00:13:51,625
[laughs] Where is their mother?

244
00:13:51,708 --> 00:13:53,750
Someone wrung their mother's neck
a while back.

245
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:56,125
- So now, they think they're donkeys.
- Huh!

246
00:13:56,208 --> 00:13:58,042
Everything's so simple for animals.

247
00:13:58,125 --> 00:14:00,625
[sniffs] I actually have
a lot of respect for them.

248
00:14:00,708 --> 00:14:03,375
I don't eat anything that has a heart.
FYI, I'm vegan.

249
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:05,208
Hm!

250
00:14:05,292 --> 00:14:06,875
Look at you!

251
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:09,583
Aren't you a sweetheart?

252
00:14:09,667 --> 00:14:11,250
He's Topsy-Turvy.

253
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:12,500
[Martina] Aw…

254
00:14:12,583 --> 00:14:13,958
This is our kitchen.

255
00:14:14,042 --> 00:14:15,542
[liquid trickling]

256
00:14:18,125 --> 00:14:20,333
Sorry, everyone lives
in their own little world here.

257
00:14:20,417 --> 00:14:21,417
[Martina chuckles]

258
00:14:22,167 --> 00:14:24,542
What the fuck? Why did you close the door?

259
00:14:25,708 --> 00:14:26,708
Martina…

260
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:30,250
- Hm!
- You're disgusting.

261
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:32,125
Pleasure to meet you.

262
00:14:32,208 --> 00:14:34,500
Tell her she's very pretty.

263
00:14:34,583 --> 00:14:36,250
He says your hair looks stupid.

264
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:37,750
Hm…

265
00:14:38,292 --> 00:14:40,500
Why didn't you tell me
you had a hot brother?

266
00:14:40,583 --> 00:14:41,958
What did she say?

267
00:14:42,042 --> 00:14:45,208
That's none of your business,
and go wash your hands like a human.

268
00:14:45,792 --> 00:14:47,125
- [snarls]
- [sighs]

269
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:48,792
[Martina chuckles]

270
00:14:48,875 --> 00:14:50,167
- C'mon.
- Hey!

271
00:14:50,250 --> 00:14:53,417
- Do not hit on my brother, okay?
- Why? Why not!

272
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:56,542
How do you say,
"I like you a lot" in Sign Language?

273
00:14:57,625 --> 00:14:59,083
- "I."
- "You."

274
00:14:59,167 --> 00:15:00,208
"Like you."

275
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:01,750
"Like you."

276
00:15:02,292 --> 00:15:03,292
"A lot."

277
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:05,500
- "A lot."
- [both chuckle]

278
00:15:05,583 --> 00:15:08,458
- [rhythmic thumping]
- [panting, moaning]

279
00:15:08,542 --> 00:15:11,208
[laughs] What the hell?
Is your brother watching porn?

280
00:15:11,292 --> 00:15:12,708
No. It's my parents.

281
00:15:13,375 --> 00:15:15,125
- Are they doing it?
- Yes.

282
00:15:15,208 --> 00:15:17,000
[upbeat folksy music playing]

283
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:19,792
[bed frame thumping and clattering]

284
00:15:24,042 --> 00:15:25,167
Mama! Papa!

285
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:28,417
The gynecologist told you not to do that!

286
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,167
And I have company.

287
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:31,917
Is your boyfriend here?

288
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:33,833
No.

289
00:15:33,875 --> 00:15:35,167
Then turn the light off!

290
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:36,250
[sighs]

291
00:15:37,167 --> 00:15:38,292
Again?

292
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:40,875
- You sure you're ready to meet my parents?
- Oh, I can't wait!

293
00:15:40,958 --> 00:15:45,167
Good evening! Nice to meet you.
And they're ignoring me…

294
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:47,083
That's because they're totally deaf.

295
00:15:47,167 --> 00:15:50,792
And if you sign without them watching,
they won't "hear" you. Just do this…

296
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:53,125
Hello!

297
00:15:57,333 --> 00:15:59,042
Good evening.

298
00:15:59,125 --> 00:16:00,917
It's nice to meet you.

299
00:16:01,417 --> 00:16:02,458
I'm, uh…

300
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,000
Mar…

301
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:06,000
Tina!

302
00:16:06,083 --> 00:16:08,625
- Howdy, Marti.
- [Martina] Howdy, Francesco.

303
00:16:08,708 --> 00:16:10,583
At last, you brought a friend!

304
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,792
Why did she say I'm a wanker?

305
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:21,958
[laughs]

306
00:16:22,042 --> 00:16:23,167
"Eat?"

307
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:25,083
He's asking if you'd like
to stay for dinner.

308
00:16:25,167 --> 00:16:26,917
Yes! I'd love it.

309
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,583
Your family's so sweet.

310
00:16:28,667 --> 00:16:30,375
[pleasant music playing]

311
00:16:30,458 --> 00:16:33,708
FYI, my mom's created a new cheese.
She's gonna want you to try it.

312
00:16:34,417 --> 00:16:35,750
Yes. I'll try it.

313
00:16:38,292 --> 00:16:39,458
Aren't you a vegan?

314
00:16:39,542 --> 00:16:42,333
Yeah, but then again,
I'm a lot of things. [Laughs]

315
00:16:47,833 --> 00:16:48,833
So?

316
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:51,125
Fucking good. [Chuckles]

317
00:16:52,875 --> 00:16:54,667
My brother has an idea.

318
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:57,708
He says he's come up
with your "Name Sign."

319
00:16:57,792 --> 00:16:58,667
My "Name Sign?"

320
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:01,750
- Martina, yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!
- Is it because he's saying "yes"?

321
00:17:03,958 --> 00:17:04,958
[chuckles]

322
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:08,250
[sniffles]

323
00:17:08,917 --> 00:17:11,333
[sobs] Fuck, I am so moved.

324
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:20,750
[music fades]

325
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:23,250
Good night. Thank you for dinner.

326
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:31,042
[upbeat folksy music playing]

327
00:17:31,125 --> 00:17:32,458
[indistinct chatter]

328
00:17:32,542 --> 00:17:33,917
[man] Ah! Here they are!

329
00:17:34,458 --> 00:17:36,792
The Musso family! [Chuckles]

330
00:17:36,875 --> 00:17:40,167
I have to say,
your husband is the luckiest man here.

331
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:41,250
[chuckles] Mwah!

332
00:17:41,750 --> 00:17:43,583
- [chuckles]
- Good morning, Mr. Mayor.

333
00:17:43,667 --> 00:17:45,958
- [mayor] Good morning.
- Care to try some homemade cheese?

334
00:17:46,042 --> 00:17:49,500
No, no, thank you. The elections
are coming up soon, as you know, and…

335
00:17:49,583 --> 00:17:52,583
Um, actually, there are some
important issues on the table.

336
00:17:52,667 --> 00:17:54,833
Especially, hm, for uh… for them.

337
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:57,500
- Who's "them?"
- Please, what I mean is…

338
00:17:57,583 --> 00:17:59,583
Oh, my! Are my eyes deceiving me?

339
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:03,292
[mayor] Here he is!
Our very own Giacinto! [Chuckles]

340
00:18:03,375 --> 00:18:06,542
[shouting] I was just, literally,
talking about you people!

341
00:18:06,625 --> 00:18:07,750
What people?

342
00:18:08,333 --> 00:18:12,333
And, actually, I was, uh,
just telling the Musso family here,

343
00:18:12,417 --> 00:18:13,708
that we…

344
00:18:13,792 --> 00:18:14,667
[Giacinto laughs]

345
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:17,625
…your friends, want to support

346
00:18:17,708 --> 00:18:19,833
our handicapped voters

347
00:18:19,917 --> 00:18:22,500
with new programs
developed by my council, okay?

348
00:18:22,583 --> 00:18:26,958
If that's what you're going to do,
then I'll see you voting day!

349
00:18:27,042 --> 00:18:28,583
Thanks! Thanks a million.

350
00:18:28,667 --> 00:18:29,917
Tell them to fuck off!

351
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:31,000
Mayor?

352
00:18:31,792 --> 00:18:34,250
My father says that
you are now obstructing access

353
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:36,083
to the table where we do business.

354
00:18:36,583 --> 00:18:37,958
Ah, certainly, yes. Uh…

355
00:18:38,042 --> 00:18:41,083
I'm always around,
so if you ever need anything. [Chuckles]

356
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:44,500
- Don't get upset and smile!
- [mayor] Well, goodbye. And thank you!

357
00:18:44,583 --> 00:18:45,875
Yes, Mama.

358
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:47,875
[students] <i>♪ Oh yeah! ♪</i>

359
00:18:47,958 --> 00:18:50,208
[Giuliana] Good!
But sing it like you mean it!

360
00:18:50,292 --> 00:18:52,458
- [bluesy piano tune playing]
- ♪ <i>Che blues! </i> ♪

361
00:18:52,542 --> 00:18:54,167
[Giuliana] Giorgia? Get ready.

362
00:18:54,875 --> 00:18:56,250
It's time for a solo.

363
00:18:56,333 --> 00:18:57,667
[students] <i>♪ Oh yeah! ♪</i>

364
00:18:57,750 --> 00:19:01,083
[vocalizing] <i>♪ Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah ♪</i>

365
00:19:01,667 --> 00:19:02,917
♪ <i>Che blues! </i> ♪

366
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,125
[Giorgia vocalizes]

367
00:19:04,208 --> 00:19:05,417
Luca, you feelin' it?

368
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:06,750
Attack and chase it!

369
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,208
<i>♪ Oh yeah ♪</i>

370
00:19:08,292 --> 00:19:12,125
- [vocalizing]
- [Giuliana] Whoo!

371
00:19:12,208 --> 00:19:13,708
- ♪ <i>Che blues! </i> ♪
- [Giuliana] Yeah!

372
00:19:13,792 --> 00:19:15,750
[Luca vocalizes]

373
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,708
Elena, now play with the tempo.

374
00:19:17,792 --> 00:19:18,667
<i>♪ Oh yeah! </i> ♪

375
00:19:18,750 --> 00:19:22,458
[scatting vocals]

376
00:19:22,542 --> 00:19:23,625
♪ <i>Che blues! </i> ♪

377
00:19:23,708 --> 00:19:27,125
[vocalizing]

378
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:29,417
- Eletta, your turn! Jump in.
<i>- ♪ Oh yeah! </i> ♪

379
00:19:30,917 --> 00:19:32,125
Go on! Jump in!!

380
00:19:33,125 --> 00:19:34,833
♪ <i>Che blues! </i> ♪

381
00:19:35,417 --> 00:19:37,458
Jump in! You got it!

382
00:19:38,292 --> 00:19:39,708
♪ <i>Oh yeah! </i> ♪

383
00:19:39,792 --> 00:19:41,708
Stop! Stop. Just hold up for a minute.

384
00:19:41,792 --> 00:19:43,333
[piano stops]

385
00:19:43,417 --> 00:19:44,458
Come over here.

386
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:49,333
Okay, now.

387
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:51,958
Let's say you won the lottery.

388
00:19:52,042 --> 00:19:53,750
Yoo-hoo!

389
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:54,833
Try that.

390
00:19:56,042 --> 00:19:57,042
[weakly] Yoo-hoo.

391
00:19:57,875 --> 00:20:00,792
You realize you should be happy
that you won? Let's help her out.

392
00:20:00,875 --> 00:20:02,542
Let's start with some blues.

393
00:20:02,625 --> 00:20:03,667
Gianfra, hit it.

394
00:20:04,167 --> 00:20:06,125
[bluesy piano tune playing]

395
00:20:06,208 --> 00:20:08,208
[class snapping in rhythm]

396
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:12,792
<i>♪ Oh yeah! ♪</i>

397
00:20:12,875 --> 00:20:13,875
You.

398
00:20:13,917 --> 00:20:14,792
♪ <i>Oh yeah! </i> ♪

399
00:20:14,875 --> 00:20:16,875
I can't hear you. Louder.

400
00:20:16,958 --> 00:20:18,333
Let them hear you!

401
00:20:18,917 --> 00:20:19,917
<i>♪ Oh yeah! ♪</i>

402
00:20:19,958 --> 00:20:22,542
[Giuliana] Ah! That's more like it.

403
00:20:22,625 --> 00:20:23,917
Keep going.

404
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,292
[Eletta] <i>♪ Oh yeah! ♪</i>

405
00:20:25,375 --> 00:20:27,250
Now, to a seventh in the chord…

406
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:28,458
[piano scale ascends]

407
00:20:28,542 --> 00:20:30,833
[higher] <i>♪ Ooh! Oh yeah! </i> ♪

408
00:20:30,917 --> 00:20:34,125
Can you sing that high?
Do you think you can sing that note? Try.

409
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:35,292
[Eletta] <i>♪ Oh yeah! ♪</i>

410
00:20:35,375 --> 00:20:37,083
Ah, now where's the energy?

411
00:20:37,167 --> 00:20:39,292
No, don't stop. You're almost there. High!

412
00:20:39,375 --> 00:20:40,375
<i>♪ Oh yeah! ♪</i>

413
00:20:40,417 --> 00:20:43,333
Up! Sing up! Let your voice
rise to the clouds. You've got it.

414
00:20:43,417 --> 00:20:44,417
Do it! Sing!

415
00:20:44,458 --> 00:20:45,375
<i>♪ Oh yeah! ♪</i>

416
00:20:45,458 --> 00:20:47,417
Good! Now make that last note very long!

417
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,500
Until you're almost out of breath!
Go on now.

418
00:20:49,583 --> 00:20:54,208
<i>♪ Oh yeah! ♪</i>

419
00:20:54,792 --> 00:20:56,500
[silence]

420
00:21:01,125 --> 00:21:02,750
[somber acoustic music plays]

421
00:21:42,167 --> 00:21:44,167
[indistinct chatter]

422
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:50,917
[Giuliana] Why sign up for Singing
if you're not gonna sing?

423
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:51,833
[music fades]

424
00:21:51,917 --> 00:21:55,042
I'm not sure if I even like singing.
I just don't know.

425
00:21:55,833 --> 00:21:57,125
Hm…

426
00:21:57,208 --> 00:21:59,167
But you like music, don't you?

427
00:22:01,125 --> 00:22:03,250
- Yes.
- Eletta, are you okay?

428
00:22:04,208 --> 00:22:05,292
[Eletta] Mm-hmm…

429
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:10,250
Wait, I have an idea. I'm gonna suggest
a duet for the end of year showcase.

430
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:12,958
- Me and him?
- [Marco] Me and her?

431
00:22:19,167 --> 00:22:20,042
Yes.

432
00:22:20,125 --> 00:22:22,708
You're both a bit shy
and a bit stuck right now.

433
00:22:22,792 --> 00:22:25,458
Spend some time together.
It'll do you both good.

434
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:30,833
Let's see…

435
00:22:32,625 --> 00:22:34,542
Both of you learn this song together.

436
00:22:36,042 --> 00:22:37,583
It's by Ron.

437
00:22:38,333 --> 00:22:40,875
If you don't know him,
believe me you'll love him.

438
00:22:40,958 --> 00:22:43,792
But, please, listen to it
before you try to sing it.

439
00:22:44,417 --> 00:22:46,542
And I mean really listen to it.

440
00:22:46,625 --> 00:22:48,833
I'll send you a link
with the backup track.

441
00:22:48,917 --> 00:22:49,958
Enjoy it, guys!

442
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:59,875
["Non abbiam bisogno di parole" playing]

443
00:23:09,083 --> 00:23:10,875
[in Italian] ♪ <i>Now come here</i>… ♪

444
00:23:14,583 --> 00:23:15,667
What were you doing?

445
00:23:15,750 --> 00:23:16,750
Nothing.

446
00:23:17,333 --> 00:23:18,333
Studying history.

447
00:23:20,083 --> 00:23:22,458
The mayor is live. It's a TV special.

448
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:27,417
<i>For your second term as mayor,
you chose to prioritize the construction</i>

449
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:29,708
<i>of a state-of-the-art
logistics center. Why, sir?</i>

450
00:23:29,792 --> 00:23:33,083
[mayor] <i>Because we must not give</i>
<i>the impression that cultivating the land</i>

451
00:23:33,167 --> 00:23:36,458
<i>or raising donkeys is prosperous enough
to keep our young people in the region.</i>

452
00:23:36,542 --> 00:23:39,083
<i>So, the logistics center
will have benefits. Any examples?</i>

453
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:42,875
[mayor] <i>Well, for Camagna,</i>
<i>we're talking about over 100 new jobs.</i>

454
00:23:42,958 --> 00:23:44,708
<i>So, there will be
economic benefits as well…</i>

455
00:23:47,667 --> 00:23:49,583
[grunting angrily]

456
00:23:50,917 --> 00:23:52,792
That asshole!

457
00:23:52,875 --> 00:23:53,958
Dad, how can we stop it?

458
00:23:54,042 --> 00:23:57,083
- I'll run in the election.
- You wanna run? Are you crazy?!

459
00:23:57,167 --> 00:23:59,250
We'll all work together!

460
00:23:59,333 --> 00:24:01,250
I'm in.

461
00:24:01,333 --> 00:24:03,333
[lavish rock music playing]

462
00:24:05,792 --> 00:24:08,250
[shouts]

463
00:24:11,417 --> 00:24:12,750
No, no. I don't want…

464
00:24:14,958 --> 00:24:16,000
[sighs]

465
00:24:22,875 --> 00:24:24,625
- [bleating]
- [quacking]

466
00:24:24,708 --> 00:24:26,250
I couldn't sleep last night.

467
00:24:27,042 --> 00:24:28,167
Why?

468
00:24:28,250 --> 00:24:31,417
It's the election.
I don't think it's a good idea.

469
00:24:32,333 --> 00:24:33,500
Because I'm Deaf?

470
00:24:33,583 --> 00:24:35,167
Yes, because you're deaf.

471
00:24:37,417 --> 00:24:38,292
[sighs]

472
00:24:38,375 --> 00:24:43,000
You know very well that being Deaf
means having an identity and a culture.

473
00:24:43,083 --> 00:24:46,792
[sighs] I know that it's not a handicap
but a culture with its own language.

474
00:24:46,875 --> 00:24:48,375
You've told me a thousand times.

475
00:24:48,458 --> 00:24:51,083
Do you want me to let that idiot
destroy everything?

476
00:24:51,167 --> 00:24:52,542
I didn't say that.

477
00:24:55,417 --> 00:24:57,417
[soft music playing]

478
00:24:57,500 --> 00:25:00,958
Being the mayor and speaking
a language that no one understands

479
00:25:01,042 --> 00:25:02,750
may seem presumptuous.

480
00:25:02,833 --> 00:25:06,542
You know the farm is our life.

481
00:25:06,625 --> 00:25:07,792
Yes, I know.

482
00:25:07,875 --> 00:25:10,667
Everyone wants money.

483
00:25:11,792 --> 00:25:16,417
But not us. We take care of animals.

484
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:20,542
Even if they speak a different language
than ours, they understand us.

485
00:25:20,625 --> 00:25:23,792
You're right. But you can't be known
as "The Mayor of Donkeys."

486
00:25:23,875 --> 00:25:25,750
Papa, the problem is your hearing.

487
00:25:26,792 --> 00:25:29,167
So, what about Elon Musk?

488
00:25:29,250 --> 00:25:30,792
What does Elon Musk have to…

489
00:25:30,875 --> 00:25:33,583
He has Asperger's Syndrome.

490
00:25:33,667 --> 00:25:35,958
And yet, he's headed to Mars!

491
00:25:36,042 --> 00:25:38,458
And he's the richest man in the world!

492
00:25:40,208 --> 00:25:44,750
Remember. Changing things
requires thinking differently.

493
00:25:45,250 --> 00:25:46,625
That's important!

494
00:25:55,542 --> 00:25:56,542
[kisses]

495
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:58,542
[music fades]

496
00:25:58,625 --> 00:25:59,625
I love you, Papa.

497
00:25:59,708 --> 00:26:00,875
Me, more.

498
00:26:02,292 --> 00:26:05,708
Even if you are flawed.

499
00:26:07,875 --> 00:26:10,292
[upbeat folksy music playing]

500
00:26:13,208 --> 00:26:14,208
You're too serious!

501
00:26:14,250 --> 00:26:15,917
Not in this one right here, no.

502
00:26:28,708 --> 00:26:30,083
[clucking, squawking]

503
00:26:30,667 --> 00:26:31,708
[shouts]

504
00:26:32,417 --> 00:26:35,792
- Good morning, Mayor.
- Ah, good morning, all of you, Mussos!

505
00:26:36,375 --> 00:26:38,792
Hey! What are you doing in there?

506
00:26:44,375 --> 00:26:45,417
I DON'T HEAR EXCUSES

507
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:47,792
- It works.
- I like it. [Chuckles]

508
