You've got my vote too! Nice, Alessandro.

751
00:41:51,250 --> 00:41:54,458
Yes! Bravo! Bravo, bravo!

752
00:41:54,542 --> 00:41:55,542
Great!

753
00:41:57,042 --> 00:41:58,500
Together, we can do this.

754
00:41:58,583 --> 00:41:59,792
[music fades]

755
00:41:59,875 --> 00:42:02,125
That's great news! Why the frown?

756
00:42:02,208 --> 00:42:05,250
How will I tend to Mama, Papa,
the farm and the market?

757
00:42:05,333 --> 00:42:07,333
And now a candidacy for mayor?!

758
00:42:08,125 --> 00:42:10,292
Stop it! We're Deaf, not stupid.

759
00:42:10,375 --> 00:42:14,167
Before you were born, we got by just fine.

760
00:42:14,250 --> 00:42:15,542
You were only 2 at the time

761
00:42:15,625 --> 00:42:16,625
So?

762
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:19,833
If you weren't always in the way,

763
00:42:19,917 --> 00:42:22,417
I'd have already completed my project!

764
00:42:22,958 --> 00:42:24,083
[exhales deeply]

765
00:42:25,458 --> 00:42:26,458
Meaning?

766
00:42:27,333 --> 00:42:29,333
I have a dream.

767
00:42:29,417 --> 00:42:32,292
To turn this place
into an educational farm

768
00:42:32,375 --> 00:42:34,417
and rent out rooms!

769
00:42:35,750 --> 00:42:36,792
Sounds good.

770
00:42:37,708 --> 00:42:38,708
But it's a dream.

771
00:42:39,500 --> 00:42:41,000
Because you underestimate me!

772
00:42:41,083 --> 00:42:43,750
I studied agriculture for a reason.

773
00:42:45,542 --> 00:42:47,208
But do you truly want to sing?

774
00:42:48,333 --> 00:42:50,167
Yeah… Maybe.

775
00:42:50,292 --> 00:42:51,875
Not, maybe. It's either yes or no!

776
00:42:52,792 --> 00:42:53,792
I do like singing…

777
00:42:53,875 --> 00:42:56,292
Then do it! And don't bust my balls!

778
00:42:58,083 --> 00:42:59,250
[sighs]

779
00:43:00,250 --> 00:43:01,417
It's a gift, you know?

780
00:43:02,083 --> 00:43:04,583
Do you even realize
that you have it? [Chuckles]

781
00:43:05,833 --> 00:43:06,833
- Hmm…
- Damn, girl!

782
00:43:06,917 --> 00:43:08,833
I have a friend who has a gift!

783
00:43:09,417 --> 00:43:10,667
I have an idea!

784
00:43:10,750 --> 00:43:12,000
What's that?

785
00:43:12,083 --> 00:43:15,208
Martina can replace you at the market.
I'll teach her sign language!

786
00:43:16,375 --> 00:43:18,500
You want her to replace me at the market?

787
00:43:19,167 --> 00:43:20,667
[laughs, gasps]

788
00:43:20,750 --> 00:43:22,542
Cool idea!

789
00:43:22,625 --> 00:43:24,667
[chuckles] I mean, why the hell not?

790
00:43:26,083 --> 00:43:28,917
My father always says
that I could sell ice to polar bears.

791
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:30,458
[laughs quietly]

792
00:43:30,542 --> 00:43:31,625
[Martina chuckles]

793
00:43:37,042 --> 00:43:38,458
[chuckles] It's a deal!

794
00:43:38,542 --> 00:43:39,625
[Martina laughs]

795
00:43:40,667 --> 00:43:41,667
Come here, you!

796
00:43:41,750 --> 00:43:42,750
Mwah!

797
00:43:43,333 --> 00:43:45,250
[laughing]

798
00:43:47,250 --> 00:43:49,542
- [Giuliana] Yes?
- Miss… may I?

799
00:43:50,625 --> 00:43:51,625
Eletta, hi.

800
00:43:52,125 --> 00:43:53,208
Come in. Come in.

801
00:43:56,458 --> 00:43:57,958
I thought about the audition.

802
00:44:02,125 --> 00:44:04,167
I wanna do it. I'll try out.

803
00:44:05,125 --> 00:44:06,208
[chuckles]

804
00:44:07,458 --> 00:44:08,458
I'm so glad.

805
00:44:09,500 --> 00:44:11,500
Really pleased.
Have you asked your parents?

806
00:44:12,208 --> 00:44:13,958
Yes, ma'am. They're very happy.

807
00:44:14,042 --> 00:44:16,167
Because you won't have time
to do <i>anything else.</i>

808
00:44:16,250 --> 00:44:18,625
We'll always be rehearsing.
Days, nights, weekends.

809
00:44:18,708 --> 00:44:20,708
We'll start tonight.
You'll come to my place.

810
00:44:20,792 --> 00:44:22,375
At six o'clock this evening.

811
00:44:22,458 --> 00:44:23,750
I'll let Marco know.

812
00:44:26,750 --> 00:44:27,875
On time, you understand?

813
00:44:32,417 --> 00:44:33,417
Thank you.

814
00:44:34,292 --> 00:44:35,292
[chuckles]

815
00:44:36,083 --> 00:44:38,250
[indistinct chatter]

816
00:44:38,333 --> 00:44:39,875
See you at the teacher's?

817
00:44:40,958 --> 00:44:43,083
[Martina] My God, he is so annoying.

818
00:44:43,583 --> 00:44:44,792
I'll see you there.

819
00:44:50,542 --> 00:44:52,792
Forget about it. Blondes are out!

820
00:44:52,875 --> 00:44:54,083
[laughs]

821
00:45:01,708 --> 00:45:04,708
["Madama Butterfly, Act 2:
Un bel dì vedremo" playing]

822
00:45:04,792 --> 00:45:06,792
[woman singing opera]

823
00:45:13,917 --> 00:45:15,750
That box belongs to my ex-husband.

824
00:45:16,375 --> 00:45:19,583
He played the cello.
And I took care of all the rest.

825
00:45:21,208 --> 00:45:22,208
What happened?

826
00:45:22,958 --> 00:45:26,208
Well, he wanted…
to call the end a "break."

827
00:45:28,250 --> 00:45:29,875
There were nine "breaks" in all.

828
00:45:29,958 --> 00:45:31,583
And I couldn't do it anymore.

829
00:45:31,667 --> 00:45:34,708
So, I told him, "Call it what you'd like,
'a Break' if you want…

830
00:45:34,792 --> 00:45:36,417
But for me, the song is finished."

831
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:38,083
And I left him.

832
00:45:38,917 --> 00:45:42,375
But I have always liked teaching,
so… here I am.

833
00:45:43,375 --> 00:45:44,500
In Alessandria?

834
00:45:44,583 --> 00:45:47,167
Let's just say I needed to put
a few hundred kilometers

835
00:45:47,250 --> 00:45:48,375
between me and his ego.

836
00:45:48,458 --> 00:45:49,875
And between me and my mother.

837
00:45:50,458 --> 00:45:53,167
But that's another chapter
in my disastrously complicated life.

838
00:45:53,250 --> 00:45:54,375
We won't go there…

839
00:45:54,458 --> 00:45:56,833
She taught me one thing
that I'm forever grateful for.

840
00:45:58,000 --> 00:46:01,167
She taught me all about music.
And how you should appreciate it.

841
00:46:01,750 --> 00:46:02,958
[chuckles]

842
00:46:07,167 --> 00:46:08,375
It's time, let's start.

843
00:46:09,458 --> 00:46:10,458
What about Marco?

844
00:46:11,042 --> 00:46:12,375
Aren't we waiting for him?

845
00:46:13,500 --> 00:46:14,875
No. Marco quit.

846
00:46:14,958 --> 00:46:15,958
He's not coming.

847
00:46:18,292 --> 00:46:19,583
Because of me?

848
00:46:21,875 --> 00:46:22,875
[Martina] Hey!

849
00:46:23,750 --> 00:46:26,625
A post about
an underground fight of his just dropped.

850
00:46:30,333 --> 00:46:31,375
It's tonight.

851
00:46:32,083 --> 00:46:33,583
- [shouting]
- Come on! Let's go!

852
00:46:34,583 --> 00:46:35,708
Bring it on!

853
00:46:35,792 --> 00:46:36,917
[dog growls]

854
00:46:37,750 --> 00:46:38,833
[barking]

855
00:46:58,625 --> 00:46:59,875
Don't be nervous.

856
00:46:59,958 --> 00:47:01,625
They bark, but they don't bite.

857
00:47:01,708 --> 00:47:03,958
Okay, that one bites. [Laughs]

858
00:47:04,042 --> 00:47:05,750
[dog barking]

859
00:47:05,833 --> 00:47:07,833
[crowd clamoring]

860
00:47:09,792 --> 00:47:11,792
[ambient melancholy music rises]

861
00:47:19,042 --> 00:47:20,625
You fuckin' pushin' me?

862
00:47:20,708 --> 00:47:22,458
- Hey! Calm down!
- Oh…

863
00:47:22,542 --> 00:47:24,417
- What the fuck you doin'?
- Come here.

864
00:47:25,292 --> 00:47:27,292
[airy vocalizations lilting]

865
00:47:28,792 --> 00:47:30,042
Back the fuck off!

866
00:47:31,667 --> 00:47:33,208
- What do you want?
- We need to talk.

867
00:47:33,292 --> 00:47:34,292
So talk, then.

868
00:47:36,208 --> 00:47:39,167
- Aren't you afraid to go in there?
- Of course, I'm afraid.

869
00:47:40,750 --> 00:47:44,292
I feel like an idiot, but… something
happened when we were practicing.

870
00:47:44,375 --> 00:47:47,125
- Eletta, I gotta go in there and prepare.
- At my place…

871
00:47:48,333 --> 00:47:51,083
- "At your place," what?
- Something happened at practice.

872
00:47:52,458 --> 00:47:53,458
[sighs]

873
00:47:54,000 --> 00:47:55,542
I've never sung like that.

874
00:48:01,208 --> 00:48:02,208
And?

875
00:48:02,708 --> 00:48:03,958
And come back and sing.

876
00:48:04,042 --> 00:48:05,042
[scoffs]

877
00:48:06,333 --> 00:48:07,875
Mark, it's time. Come on!

878
00:48:09,500 --> 00:48:11,875
Listen, singing is your path to follow.

879
00:48:13,167 --> 00:48:14,750
Don't waste time following me.

880
00:48:15,750 --> 00:48:17,667
[woman] Mark! Come on! Let's get going!

881
00:48:19,583 --> 00:48:20,583
Okay?

882
00:48:24,125 --> 00:48:25,333
Now, get outta here.

883
00:48:27,167 --> 00:48:28,167
No.

884
00:48:29,125 --> 00:48:30,333
Eletta, go.

885
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:34,375
Get outta here!

886
00:48:45,167 --> 00:48:47,667
- You're a fucking asshole!
- Yeah, fuck you too!

887
00:48:50,708 --> 00:48:52,708
[music fades]

888
00:48:58,875 --> 00:49:00,375
Mama, I'm going.

889
00:49:00,458 --> 00:49:01,667
Where are you going?

890
00:49:01,750 --> 00:49:02,958
I'll be back for dinner.

891
00:49:03,458 --> 00:49:05,542
The TV people are about to arrive.

892
00:49:05,625 --> 00:49:08,542
What do you mean, "TV people?"
No one ever told me that?

893
00:49:08,625 --> 00:49:10,375
I thought Dad had told you.

894
00:49:10,458 --> 00:49:12,625
[sighs] Can you reschedule for tomorrow?

895
00:49:12,708 --> 00:49:14,292
Impossible!

896
00:49:16,958 --> 00:49:18,792
I have to meet my boyfriend soon.

897
00:49:20,542 --> 00:49:21,875
Ah, your boyfriend!

898
00:49:21,958 --> 00:49:25,125
Get him to come here!
He's part of the family, now.

899
00:49:25,625 --> 00:49:27,917
Mama, I would,
but we have work we can't do here.

900
00:49:28,000 --> 00:49:29,292
You can do them here.

901
00:49:29,375 --> 00:49:32,000
He'll be proud to see
his father-in-law become mayor!

902
00:49:34,208 --> 00:49:35,667
[rooster crowing]

903
00:49:35,750 --> 00:49:37,042
Okay, they're here.

904
00:49:37,125 --> 00:49:38,375
Go on downstairs.

905
00:49:38,458 --> 00:49:41,167
[upbeat folksy music playing]

906
00:49:41,250 --> 00:49:43,208
[braying]

907
00:49:46,208 --> 00:49:47,458
[horn beeps]

908
00:49:56,958 --> 00:49:57,875
Hello!

909
00:49:57,958 --> 00:50:00,000
Who is she?

910
00:50:04,625 --> 00:50:06,042
It's beautiful here.

911
00:50:07,583 --> 00:50:08,667
Oh, that's too much.

912
00:50:10,042 --> 00:50:13,042
It's a beautiful farm.
And the lighting is just perfect.

913
00:50:16,250 --> 00:50:19,667
Her look is completely wrong, though.
Does she have something rustic?

914
00:50:19,750 --> 00:50:22,667
Something that says, "donkey farm?"
And, lose the makeup.

915
00:50:23,458 --> 00:50:25,708
She says you're not going
to a beauty contest.

916
00:50:25,792 --> 00:50:27,833
She wants to shoot us working the farm.

917
00:50:27,917 --> 00:50:29,250
Let's go change.

918
00:50:31,917 --> 00:50:35,333
Sorry, but is she from the TV?

919
00:50:38,542 --> 00:50:39,583
Stop! Come on!

920
00:50:44,375 --> 00:50:45,750
[music fades]

921
00:50:45,833 --> 00:50:49,625
Mr. Musso, you're running
in the local municipal elections.

922
00:50:49,708 --> 00:50:52,042
Can you tell us why you would want to?

923
00:50:52,125 --> 00:50:53,167
[cell phone pings]

924
00:50:54,292 --> 00:50:56,417
Camagna is a town of 500 residents.

925
00:50:58,542 --> 00:51:00,667
So far, we've farmed the land
and raised animals.

926
00:51:02,458 --> 00:51:04,333
[thunder rumbling]

927
00:51:04,417 --> 00:51:06,792
Today, someone wants to intervene.

928
00:51:06,875 --> 00:51:08,542
I WILL BE AT THE LESSON THIS AFTERNOON

929
00:51:08,625 --> 00:51:12,167
They say our produce isn't sufficient.
That we can produce more

930
00:51:12,250 --> 00:51:14,292
to reach the global market.

931
00:51:15,792 --> 00:51:17,542
I'M SORRY, I'll BE LATE TONIGHT…

932
00:51:18,417 --> 00:51:22,917
You can already feel the smog,
and everything is moving faster.

933
00:51:26,750 --> 00:51:28,750
I want to bring a new energy to Camagna.

934
00:51:32,750 --> 00:51:34,125
Hm. Mm.

935
00:51:34,208 --> 00:51:35,917
Uh… You're deaf, sir.

936
00:51:36,000 --> 00:51:39,250
Don't you think that could be
a handicap as the town's mayor?

937
00:51:42,792 --> 00:51:44,375
Handicap? How dare you?

938
00:51:44,458 --> 00:51:45,458
[pinging]

939
00:51:47,500 --> 00:51:49,684
And you, with that setup?
You think you're a journalist?

940
00:51:49,708 --> 00:51:51,417
- Is he angry now?
- No-no.

941
00:51:52,083 --> 00:51:53,958
- You sure about that?
- Yeah.

942
00:51:54,042 --> 00:51:56,458
If you're a journalist, I can be mayor!

943
00:51:57,208 --> 00:51:59,375
So, he doesn't believe it's a handicap?

944
00:52:00,125 --> 00:52:01,000
No.

945
00:52:01,083 --> 00:52:03,042
GET HERE IN HALF AN HOUR
OR STAY WHERE YOU ARE

946
00:52:03,125 --> 00:52:04,125
IT'S NOT UP TO ME

947
00:52:07,583 --> 00:52:10,042
Ah! A new boyfriend! I got that part.

948
00:52:11,958 --> 00:52:13,083
Did you translate?

949
00:52:13,167 --> 00:52:14,833
I'm translating like always!

950
00:52:14,917 --> 00:52:17,542
Are you sure you translated?
You've got your face in your phone…

951
00:52:18,625 --> 00:52:19,958
Who are you texting?

952
00:52:20,625 --> 00:52:21,708
[stomping]

953
00:52:21,792 --> 00:52:23,917
Your behavior's not appropriate.

954
00:52:24,500 --> 00:52:27,250
I missed my date with my boyfriend.

955
00:52:27,333 --> 00:52:30,250
Everything always
has to revolve around you!

956
00:52:30,333 --> 00:52:32,292
And you don't care about my life.

957
00:52:32,833 --> 00:52:34,792
What's that got to do with anything?

958
00:52:34,875 --> 00:52:35,875
[stomping]

959
00:52:35,958 --> 00:52:37,583
[ambient melancholy music rises]

960
00:52:37,667 --> 00:52:38,542
Can we go on?

961
00:52:38,625 --> 00:52:42,292
Translate properly now, word for word.

962
00:52:42,375 --> 00:52:43,792
Translate!

963
00:52:43,875 --> 00:52:45,583
Look at me.

964
00:52:47,958 --> 00:52:49,042
I will sign…

965
00:52:50,500 --> 00:52:53,000
- Francesco will write my answers.
- Ah, hm…

966
00:52:53,083 --> 00:52:55,042
[distant thunder rumbling]

967
00:52:57,583 --> 00:52:59,583
You will subtitle what I say.

968
00:52:59,667 --> 00:53:00,667
Okay.

969
00:53:04,958 --> 00:53:08,125
And if you speak slowly,
I can easily read your lips.

970
00:53:08,208 --> 00:53:09,750
Okay. Mm.

971
00:53:10,250 --> 00:53:13,417
If we don't understand each other,
we'll write it down.

972
00:53:13,500 --> 00:53:15,583
Perfect! I got it.

973
00:53:35,417 --> 00:53:38,500
Now then, what do you want
to do for Cama… No?

974
00:53:44,667 --> 00:53:45,542
Okay.

975
00:53:45,625 --> 00:53:49,083
[shouting] And what do you want…

976
00:54:07,667 --> 00:54:09,667
[cell phone vibrating]

977
00:54:15,917 --> 00:54:17,333
[buzzing]

978
00:54:18,458 --> 00:54:20,250
[quick piano tune playing]

979
00:54:20,333 --> 00:54:21,958
- [door buzzes]
- [playing stops]

980
00:54:23,292 --> 00:54:24,542
[Eletta] Professor?!

981
00:54:25,542 --> 00:54:27,250
It's me, Eletta!

982
00:54:29,292 --> 00:54:31,250
Please! It wasn't my fault!

983
00:54:48,333 --> 00:54:51,583
[buzzing repetitively]

984
00:54:56,667 --> 00:54:58,667
[piano continues playing]

985
00:55:21,375 --> 00:55:22,750
[rhythmic thumping]

986
00:55:26,125 --> 00:55:27,792
[loud thumping]

987
00:55:33,625 --> 00:55:36,042
You were terrible!

988
00:55:37,500 --> 00:55:39,250
Apologize to your father.

989
00:55:40,583 --> 00:55:43,292
Apologize to my father?
For what exactly? For wanting a life?

990
00:55:43,375 --> 00:55:45,708
You're not the only girl
in the world with a boyfriend.

991
00:55:45,792 --> 00:55:50,000
There are lots like you. But remember
that you have responsibilities.

992
00:55:50,083 --> 00:55:52,375
Your boyfriend comes after them.

993
00:55:52,458 --> 00:55:53,583
Apologize!

994
00:55:53,667 --> 00:55:55,417
Mama, I don't have a boyfriend.

995
00:55:55,500 --> 00:55:57,542
And if we keep this up, I never will.

996
00:56:01,958 --> 00:56:03,958
[thunder rumbling]

997
00:56:11,750 --> 00:56:14,042
I have something to tell you
that's really important.

998
00:56:14,125 --> 00:56:15,667
Are you pregnant?

999
00:56:17,875 --> 00:56:20,375
No! I don't have a boyfriend, I told you.

1000
00:56:25,708 --> 00:56:29,500
Okay, here it is. I'm training to get
into a school for professional singers.

1001
00:56:29,583 --> 00:56:32,083
If I'm accepted,
I'll finish my studies there.

1002
00:56:32,667 --> 00:56:35,417
My teacher says that I have talent,
that I can make it.

1003
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:38,917
I go to her place every night.
She's helping me prepare.

1004
00:56:41,083 --> 00:56:43,542
If I pass the audition,
I'll move to Turin.

1005
00:56:46,375 --> 00:56:48,625
You really want to move to Turin?

1006
00:56:48,708 --> 00:56:50,708
[thunder rumbling]

1007
00:56:50,792 --> 00:56:53,083
So you won't be at home with us anymore?

1008
00:56:53,708 --> 00:56:54,875
If I'm accepted.

1009
00:56:56,458 --> 00:56:58,375
How long have you been singing?

1010
00:57:02,458 --> 00:57:03,750
More than three months.

1011
00:57:04,417 --> 00:57:06,458
I'm also in the school choir.

1012
00:57:07,917 --> 00:57:08,917
[smacking table]

1013
00:57:09,000 --> 00:57:11,042
What's this teacher's name?

1014
00:57:11,750 --> 00:57:12,750
Giuliana.

1015
00:57:12,792 --> 00:57:13,792
And her last name?

1016
00:57:14,625 --> 00:57:18,750
Her last name is Dickhead!
She's brainwashed you!

1017
00:57:19,458 --> 00:57:22,667
Don't you have anything to say?

1018
00:57:23,875 --> 00:57:24,708
Mama!

1019
00:57:24,792 --> 00:57:27,583
I like singing,
and Giuliana says I'm very good.

1020
00:57:30,458 --> 00:57:32,042
Ah, I get it.

1021
00:57:35,333 --> 00:57:36,708
What do you think you get?

1022
00:57:36,792 --> 00:57:38,792
You set it all up.

1023
00:57:38,875 --> 00:57:41,792
You figured it all out in secret.

1024
00:57:43,792 --> 00:57:47,583
No, Mom. It's not like that.
She wanted to tell you sooner.

1025
00:57:47,667 --> 00:57:49,917
You are the problem.

1026
00:57:53,583 --> 00:57:56,292
So, that means we're the problem?

1027
00:57:56,375 --> 00:57:57,750
Papa, it's all of it.

1028
00:57:57,833 --> 00:58:01,292
All of it. It's the farm,
the market, now the election…

1029
00:58:05,125 --> 00:58:06,500
I'm here too!

1030
00:58:07,125 --> 00:58:11,125
You've always told me
we Deaf people are better than others.

1031
00:58:11,208 --> 00:58:15,375
But actually you two
have never had faith in me!

1032
00:58:15,458 --> 00:58:18,542
You should be ashamed!

1033
00:58:18,625 --> 00:58:19,958
He has a point.

1034
00:58:20,042 --> 00:58:21,500
I can stand up for myself!

1035
00:58:29,792 --> 00:58:31,292
[Alessandro sighs]

1036
00:58:34,042 --> 00:58:35,375
Say something to her!

1037
00:58:36,250 --> 00:58:38,917
I'm beat. I'm going to bed.

1038
00:58:40,167 --> 00:58:41,583
Going to bed? Already?

1039
00:58:42,458 --> 00:58:43,458
Papa!

1040
00:58:43,917 --> 00:58:44,958
Papa!

1041
00:58:45,583 --> 00:58:47,583
[Alessandro exhales deeply]

1042
00:58:50,000 --> 00:58:52,292
Are you happy? See what you've done?

1043
00:58:52,375 --> 00:58:54,125
No, Mama, I'm not happy at all!

1044
00:58:54,208 --> 00:58:56,125
I'd have to leave here to be happy!

1045
00:58:56,208 --> 00:58:58,708
[ambient melancholy music plays softly]

1046
00:58:58,792 --> 00:59:01,250
[grunting gently]

1047
00:59:19,458 --> 00:59:21,583
HOW TO BE A LEADER

1048
00:59:27,792 --> 00:59:31,125
Our daughter wants to be a singer,
and you're just standing there!

1049
00:59:32,042 --> 00:59:34,500
If she wants to be a singer,
we should let her.

1050
00:59:34,583 --> 00:59:38,292
So she can show her ass
to the whole world.

1051
00:59:38,375 --> 00:59:42,250
Since when have you been such a bigot?

1052
00:59:43,208 --> 00:59:45,708
Don't you understand, she's in danger?

1053
00:59:45,792 --> 00:59:47,875
And you're just there…

1054
00:59:48,708 --> 00:59:51,583
You have to tell her to stay here.

1055
00:59:52,417 --> 00:59:54,875
What if she doesn't have
a beautiful voice?

1056
00:59:54,958 --> 00:59:58,250
It's that Giuliana
who put that idea in her head.

1057
00:59:59,625 --> 01:00:04,208
Stop being silly. Enough!
Stop talking nonsense!

1058
01:00:04,292 --> 01:00:06,500
Our daughter isn't stupid.

1059
01:00:07,375 --> 01:00:10,042
You're the one with issues.

1060
01:00:10,125 --> 01:00:13,083
Okay. Let's say she gets in.

1061
01:00:13,167 --> 01:00:15,292
How do we manage here?

1062
01:00:15,375 --> 01:00:19,042
Oh, so the problem isn't that
our daughter is going to Turin.

1063
01:00:19,125 --> 01:00:21,667
But that the two of us will be here alone.

1064
01:00:24,750 --> 01:00:26,542
Come here.

1065
01:00:27,667 --> 01:00:29,250
Look at me!

1066
01:00:32,125 --> 01:00:35,042
I'm sure that Eletta will miss us…

1067
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:37,375
And come back.

1068
01:00:39,083 --> 01:00:43,083
Please, tell her to stay.

1069
01:00:44,708 --> 01:00:46,708
Of course.

1070
01:00:47,292 --> 01:00:48,208
[sighs]

1071
01:00:48,292 --> 01:00:50,292
[bright tranquil music plays]

1072
01:00:55,917 --> 01:00:57,917
[car engine starts]

1073
01:01:01,167 --> 01:01:03,167
[bright vocalizations lilting]

1074
01:01:06,583 --> 01:01:09,500
[Martina] I'm here! Sorry I'm late!

1075
01:01:09,583 --> 01:01:10,750
Fuck.

1076
01:01:20,500 --> 01:01:21,500
[music fades]

1077
01:01:21,583 --> 01:01:23,958
[Giuliana] Good morning.
Thank you for being on time.

1078
01:01:24,042 --> 01:01:26,958
Please, relax and make yourself at home.
You're all good.

1079
01:01:27,625 --> 01:01:30,667
- I wasn't on time yesterday because…
- Did I ask you to explain?

1080
01:01:31,833 --> 01:01:32,917
I apologize.

1081
01:01:36,292 --> 01:01:37,500
Come over here.

1082
01:01:44,708 --> 01:01:46,750
["Un'emozione da poco" plays on phone]

1083
01:01:46,833 --> 01:01:49,125
Anna Oxa. You know her?

1084
01:01:49,208 --> 01:01:50,500
No.

1085
01:01:50,583 --> 01:01:53,458
What is the matter with kids these days?
It was 1978. She was 16.

1086
01:01:53,542 --> 01:01:56,750
She went to the Sanremo Festival,
briefcase in hand, dressed as a man,

1087
01:01:56,833 --> 01:01:58,873
and she walked on stage,
put the case on the ground,

1088
01:01:58,917 --> 01:02:01,000
turned her back to the audience,
and sang like this!

1089
01:02:01,083 --> 01:02:03,583
[in Italian] <i>♪ There is a reason</i>
<i>Growing in me ♪</i>

1090
01:02:03,667 --> 01:02:04,542
Perfect start.

1091
01:02:04,625 --> 01:02:05,500
[power chord]

1092
01:02:05,583 --> 01:02:08,208
[mouthing Italian lyrics]
<i>♪ And my naivety's fading ♪</i>

1093
01:02:09,042 --> 01:02:11,000
- [power chords]
<i>- ♪ And like a journey… ♪</i>

1094
01:02:11,083 --> 01:02:13,250
- [music stops]
- Hey, what are you doing?

1095
01:02:13,333 --> 01:02:17,292
- You said I have a gift. Are you sure?
- You can doubt everything in this world.

1096
01:02:17,375 --> 01:02:18,458
Except for me.

1097
01:02:18,958 --> 01:02:21,625
[in Italian] <i>♪ …in the night, it ends ♪</i>

1098
01:02:21,708 --> 01:02:24,958
<i>♪ Tell me, tell me, tell me
What sense it makes ♪</i>

1099
01:02:25,917 --> 01:02:29,250
<i>♪ To give love to a man who has no mercy ♪</i>

1100
01:02:30,000 --> 01:02:31,375
- [power chords]
- [both laugh]

1101
01:02:31,458 --> 01:02:33,792
♪ <i>One who never felt defeated </i> ♪

1102
01:02:33,875 --> 01:02:37,292
- Then she danced. Here comes the chorus…
- ♪ <i>Who never lost, never </i> ♪

1103
01:02:37,375 --> 01:02:40,250
<i>♪ For you, for you… ♪</i>

1104
01:02:40,333 --> 01:02:41,917
[indistinct chatter]

1105
01:02:42,000 --> 01:02:43,000
Good morning.

1106
01:02:44,958 --> 01:02:48,292
What's so special about this donkey milk
that it costs €20 a liter?

1107
01:02:48,375 --> 01:02:51,250
- Why aren't all cars the same price?
- It depends on their features.

1108
01:02:51,333 --> 01:02:55,458
A donkey isn't a cow. It produces a small
amount of milk, but it's high quality.

1109
01:02:56,125 --> 01:02:59,375
To me, it seems like a gimmick
to steal people's money.

1110
01:02:59,458 --> 01:03:03,042
Did you wake up this morning and say,
"Today, I'm gonna be an asshole?"

1111
01:03:04,083 --> 01:03:05,417
He's a fucking asshole!

1112
01:03:06,417 --> 01:03:07,667
I can try it?

1113
01:03:18,958 --> 01:03:19,958
Like I said.

1114
01:03:20,667 --> 01:03:22,417
Hm.It's just a gimmick.

1115
01:03:27,042 --> 01:03:28,750
[upbeat folksy music plays]

1116
01:03:29,333 --> 01:03:31,958
- Bumpkins…
- What the hell are you looking at?!

1117
01:03:34,125 --> 01:03:35,375
[straining]

1118
01:03:35,958 --> 01:03:36,958
[groans]

1119
01:03:44,708 --> 01:03:46,708
[music fades]

1120
01:03:48,458 --> 01:03:50,625
So, tell me, how'd it go at the market?

1121
01:03:50,708 --> 01:03:52,000
Zero!

1122
01:03:52,958 --> 01:03:54,292
You didn't sell anything?

1123
01:03:54,375 --> 01:03:57,292
I don't sell anymore, don't fuck anymore,
and I beat people up.

1124
01:03:57,375 --> 01:04:00,250
You don't sell or fuck anymore,
but you attack people? What happened?

1125
01:04:00,875 --> 01:04:02,750
It's your fault!

1126
01:04:02,833 --> 01:04:04,083
Me?!

1127
01:04:04,167 --> 01:04:06,042
Martina's a disaster.

1128
01:04:06,125 --> 01:04:07,625
And you're gonna blame that on me?

1129
01:04:07,708 --> 01:04:09,708
She has to be kind. She's not polite!

1130
01:04:09,792 --> 01:04:13,125
But that's normal. She just started.
Mama! She just needs some time.

1131
01:04:13,208 --> 01:04:15,458
If she doesn't work out,
then it's your fault.

1132
01:04:15,542 --> 01:04:17,458
You keep people at arm's length.

1133
01:04:17,542 --> 01:04:20,792
You make no effort to accept
those that you call "The Others."

1134
01:04:21,625 --> 01:04:22,542
[sighs]

1135
01:04:22,625 --> 01:04:24,625
[sweet plucky music playing]

1136
01:04:30,792 --> 01:04:32,375
[Martina] What do you wanna do?

1137
01:04:40,875 --> 01:04:41,958
[softly] Kiss?

1138
01:04:48,583 --> 01:04:50,792
[Martina speaking quietly]

1139
01:04:50,875 --> 01:04:51,917
[sighs]

1140
01:04:56,250 --> 01:04:58,708
[laughing] You're crazy…

1141
01:05:03,958 --> 01:05:07,833
Sorry again for yesterday, but that
market's like a magnet for assholes.

1142
01:05:07,917 --> 01:05:09,000
Forget about it.

1143
01:05:11,125 --> 01:05:13,125
[clamoring in hallway]

1144
01:05:21,583 --> 01:05:23,167
[Martina] What's going on?

1145
01:05:23,250 --> 01:05:25,917
That guy's been involved
in some illegal fights.

1146
01:05:26,750 --> 01:05:27,750
Who is it?

1147
01:05:27,833 --> 01:05:29,833
[indistinct chattering]

1148
01:05:30,667 --> 01:05:32,917
-[girl] They want information
-[boy] Figures… It's Marco.

1149
01:05:33,000 --> 01:05:36,250
Police wanna question him about some
underground fights he's involved with.

1150
01:05:40,000 --> 01:05:41,542
They're arresting him?

1151
01:05:41,625 --> 01:05:42,875
What do you think?

1152
01:05:47,125 --> 01:05:49,125
[gentle piano melody playing]

1153
01:05:50,833 --> 01:05:52,583
[in Italian] <i>♪ I'd like ♪</i>

1154
01:05:53,750 --> 01:05:57,667
<i>♪ To give you my word</i>
<i>To tell you I can't wait </i> ♪

1155
01:05:57,750 --> 01:06:00,208
<i>♪ To forget everything ♪</i>

1156
01:06:00,875 --> 01:06:02,667
- ♪ <i>I would like… </i> ♪
- [music stops]

1157
01:06:02,750 --> 01:06:04,417
Eletta, you're not singing.

1158
01:06:04,500 --> 01:06:08,458
You're whining. You're not thinking about
what you're singing, you're not breathing…

1159
01:06:08,542 --> 01:06:12,167
I've been practicing all week, Miss.
You didn't focus like this on Marco.

1160
01:06:12,250 --> 01:06:13,250
What?

1161
01:06:13,833 --> 01:06:16,750
If Marco had kept singing,
he might have avoided the trouble he's in.

1162
01:06:16,833 --> 01:06:18,208
He's not why you're here.

1163
01:06:19,333 --> 01:06:20,750
Or why I'm here.

1164
01:06:24,667 --> 01:06:27,750
Why don't you just leave?
Do me a favor and just leave.

1165
01:06:27,833 --> 01:06:30,292
Today is ruined.
It's ruined. And you know what?

1166
01:06:30,375 --> 01:06:32,625
Think carefully about
whether you want this.

1167
01:06:38,042 --> 01:06:39,667
[quietly] I don't believe this.

1168
01:06:46,625 --> 01:06:49,875
Okay, yes, I'll be back
to see you tomorrow. Eh…

1169
01:06:53,417 --> 01:06:54,542
You good?

1170
01:06:56,667 --> 01:06:58,625
What was Giacinto doing here?

1171
01:07:02,625 --> 01:07:05,500
Tomorrow at 6 p.m.,
we have a meeting with the voters.

1172
01:07:05,583 --> 01:07:08,917
Mom's asked Giacinto to give us a hand.

1173
01:07:09,000 --> 01:07:12,417
But you always said the Oralists
were a disgrace to the non-hearing.

1174
01:07:12,500 --> 01:07:15,667
We need to get by on our own from now on.

1175
01:07:15,750 --> 01:07:16,833
You serious now?

1176
01:07:16,917 --> 01:07:17,958
Of course.

1177
01:07:18,500 --> 01:07:21,208
[ambient melancholy music playing]

1178
01:07:24,458 --> 01:07:27,250
HOW LONG WILL YOU BE AWAY FROM SCHOOL?

1179
01:07:27,333 --> 01:07:31,667
MARCO: TWO MONTHS I THINK.
IF I BEHAVE MAYBE LESS

1180
01:07:32,792 --> 01:07:35,167
[keys clacking]

1181
01:07:37,000 --> 01:07:39,250
THEN BEHAVE. SO YOU CAN KEEP SINGING

1182
01:07:39,333 --> 01:07:42,250
YOU'RE OBSESSED WITH SINGING

1183
01:07:45,250 --> 01:07:47,500
[keys clacking]

1184
01:07:48,833 --> 01:07:51,417
YES. SINGING MAKES ME FEEL GOOD.
I DISCOVERED THAT WITH YOU.

1185
01:07:51,500 --> 01:07:54,917
THEN SING AS MUCH AS YOU CAN

1186
01:07:56,750 --> 01:07:57,833
[exhales heavily]

1187
01:07:57,917 --> 01:07:59,917
[music fades]

1188
01:08:00,792 --> 01:08:03,625
[Eletta in Italian]
<i>♪ There is a reason growing in me ♪</i>

1189
01:08:04,417 --> 01:08:07,042
<i>- ♪ And my naivety's fading ♪</i>
- [power chords playing]

1190
01:08:09,042 --> 01:08:11,833
♪ <i>And like a journey in the night</i>
<i>It ends </i> ♪

1191
01:08:11,917 --> 01:08:14,958
<i>♪ Tell me, tell me, tell me
What sense it makes ♪</i>

1192
01:08:15,042 --> 01:08:16,292
More!

1193
01:08:16,375 --> 01:08:18,917
♪ <i>To give love to a man who has no mercy </i> ♪

1194
01:08:19,000 --> 01:08:20,625
[accompanying piano continues]

1195
01:08:20,708 --> 01:08:23,792
<i>- ♪ One who never felt defeated ♪</i>
- Yes!

1196
01:08:23,875 --> 01:08:26,792
<i>- ♪ Who never lost, never ♪</i>
- Now, softly!

1197
01:08:26,875 --> 01:08:28,167
♪ <i>For you, for you… </i> ♪

1198
01:08:28,250 --> 01:08:30,500
Oh! Red! [Chuckles]

1199
01:08:30,583 --> 01:08:33,250
<i>♪ A song ♪</i>

1200
01:08:34,917 --> 01:08:39,500
♪ <i>Never a cheap illusion</i>
<i>A banal thought </i> ♪

1201
01:08:39,583 --> 01:08:41,375
<i>♪ Something that remains ♪</i>

1202
01:08:41,458 --> 01:08:44,167
♪ <i>Instead, for me </i> ♪

1203
01:08:44,250 --> 01:08:45,500
- ♪ <i>For me </i> ♪
- Francesco?

1204
01:08:45,583 --> 01:08:49,042
<i>- ♪ It's more than normal ♪</i>
- He went to get Martina. He'll be here.

1205
01:08:50,375 --> 01:08:53,250
♪ <i>That such a slight emotion </i> ♪

1206
01:08:53,333 --> 01:08:55,042
<i>♪ Can make me feel this bad ♪</i>

1207
01:08:55,125 --> 01:08:58,667
- Slowly! Just like that!
<i>- ♪ One softly-spoken word is enough ♪</i>

1208
01:08:58,750 --> 01:09:01,333
<i>♪ And I can no longer see reality ♪</i>

1209
01:09:01,417 --> 01:09:02,417
[Giuliana] Breathe…

1210
01:09:02,458 --> 01:09:05,208
[both] ♪ <i>I don't know</i>
<i>Where it is anymore </i> ♪

1211
01:09:06,250 --> 01:09:09,292
♪ <i>The clear difference </i> ♪

1212
01:09:09,375 --> 01:09:13,792
<i>♪ Between the blindest love
And the stupidest patience ♪</i>

1213
01:09:13,875 --> 01:09:17,917
<i>♪ No, I can no longer see reality ♪</i>

1214
01:09:18,000 --> 01:09:20,875
♪ <i>Nor how much tenderness it gives you ♪</i>

1215
01:09:21,708 --> 01:09:24,750
<i>♪ My incoherence ♪</i>

1216
01:09:24,833 --> 01:09:29,208
<i>♪ Thinking that you would live
Just fine without ♪</i>

1217
01:09:29,292 --> 01:09:30,458
[music stops]

1218
01:09:33,500 --> 01:09:36,667
Concretely, uh, what do you plan
to do about our young people?

1219
01:09:36,750 --> 01:09:39,167
Without any employment
development in the area,

1220
01:09:39,250 --> 01:09:41,167
many of them are packing up and leaving.

1221
01:09:41,250 --> 01:09:42,583
Everyone is leaving.

1222
01:09:43,958 --> 01:09:46,250
Let them go sing, the young people!

1223
01:09:46,333 --> 01:09:47,833
[man] What's that gotta do with it?

1224
01:09:47,917 --> 01:09:51,083
Our small world is part of a bigger world
that's moving very fast!

1225
01:09:51,167 --> 01:09:53,042
- We have to keep up with it!
- [clamoring]

1226
01:09:53,125 --> 01:09:54,375
What do you think?

1227
01:09:54,458 --> 01:09:55,375
It's a problem.

1228
01:09:55,458 --> 01:09:57,625
[crowd clamoring]

1229
01:09:57,708 --> 01:09:58,625
[chuckles]

1230
01:09:58,708 --> 01:10:01,083
"What are ya? Papa and Mama ducks?"

1231
01:10:01,167 --> 01:10:02,333
What did you call me?

1232
01:10:02,958 --> 01:10:05,542
[gasps] Holy shit, you almost spilled it!

1233
01:10:06,125 --> 01:10:07,458
[overlapping shouts]

1234
01:10:20,833 --> 01:10:22,625
You scared me.

1235
01:10:22,708 --> 01:10:24,208
You want to see me dead?

1236
01:10:24,292 --> 01:10:26,958
Is it somehow <i>my fault</i>
that they had an accident?

1237
01:10:27,667 --> 01:10:30,292
Who introduced him to Martina?
It's your fault!

1238
01:10:31,542 --> 01:10:34,667
And you, what are you doing
while you're driving?

1239
01:10:36,250 --> 01:10:37,792
[stifling laughter]

1240
01:10:37,875 --> 01:10:38,875
[laughing]

1241
01:10:38,958 --> 01:10:40,333
So? What were you doing?

1242
01:10:42,250 --> 01:10:43,583
You're a little girl…

1243
01:10:43,667 --> 01:10:45,458
Come on! C'mon, tell me!

1244
01:10:45,542 --> 01:10:47,542
- [groans]
- Oh, God. Sorry. Sorry.

1245
01:10:47,625 --> 01:10:50,333
[laughs] Come on, I'm sorry.
Please? Forgive me.

1246
01:10:50,417 --> 01:10:52,208
- [Francesco] No.
- [laughs] Come on!

1247
01:10:56,250 --> 01:10:57,833
All traitors!

1248
01:10:57,917 --> 01:11:00,167
You can't call them that
They're your voters.

1249
01:11:00,250 --> 01:11:02,125
No. I'm talking about you.

1250
01:11:02,208 --> 01:11:04,042
You left me there on my own.

1251
01:11:04,125 --> 01:11:07,375
Francesco had a car accident,
and we had to go and get him.

1252
01:11:07,458 --> 01:11:08,667
It's not serious.

1253
01:11:08,750 --> 01:11:11,583
He sprained his wrist.
He's in his room resting.

1254
01:11:11,667 --> 01:11:12,958
And Mom?

1255
01:11:14,083 --> 01:11:15,083
I don't know.

1256
01:11:18,958 --> 01:11:20,958
[soft tones rising gently]

1257
01:11:23,500 --> 01:11:24,500
Mama!

1258
01:11:25,500 --> 01:11:26,500
Mama?

1259
01:11:28,083 --> 01:11:29,458
Mama, sit up.

1260
01:11:29,542 --> 01:11:30,542
[grunts]

1261
01:11:32,958 --> 01:11:34,875
Leave me alone. Don't touch me.

1262
01:11:34,958 --> 01:11:38,083
Leave me alone! Here, with the cheese.

1263
01:11:38,167 --> 01:11:40,208
Mama get up, you can't stay here.

1264
01:11:40,292 --> 01:11:41,792
I want to stay here!

1265
01:11:41,875 --> 01:11:43,333
Let me help you, please.

1266
01:11:44,750 --> 01:11:48,250
Help me? But I'm a terrible mother.

1267
01:11:52,375 --> 01:11:54,833
Because I'm Deaf,

1268
01:11:54,917 --> 01:11:57,458
and I couldn't find
the right words with you!

1269
01:11:57,542 --> 01:11:59,250
You're not a bad mother.

1270
01:11:59,792 --> 01:12:02,333
In fact, you're the mom
everyone wishes they had.

1271
01:12:11,542 --> 01:12:16,833
When you were born, and they told me

1272
01:12:18,333 --> 01:12:21,667
that you could hear, I cried.

1273
01:12:22,250 --> 01:12:24,250
Those like you,

1274
01:12:24,333 --> 01:12:27,250
I could never stand them!

1275
01:12:29,375 --> 01:12:34,542
But he calmed me down, saying

1276
01:12:34,625 --> 01:12:39,458
he would have raised you Deaf inside.

1277
01:12:40,083 --> 01:12:44,625
But, instead, you can hear.

1278
01:12:45,667 --> 01:12:52,167
And you want to go away to sing.

1279
01:13:04,333 --> 01:13:05,375
So that's it?

1280
01:13:07,208 --> 01:13:10,292
Am I condemned to a life
of serving the two of you forever?

1281
01:13:12,083 --> 01:13:14,583
Is that what you see
when you look at my future?

1282
01:13:17,542 --> 01:13:18,542
And you?

1283
01:13:19,958 --> 01:13:21,208
You say nothing.

1284
01:13:22,667 --> 01:13:24,667
There is no problem.

1285
01:13:25,625 --> 01:13:27,833
It's better if you go.

1286
01:13:27,917 --> 01:13:30,250
Follow your own path. You're free.

1287
01:13:33,542 --> 01:13:35,042
We'll get by on our own.

1288
01:13:51,125 --> 01:13:53,333
- Eletta? What are you doing here…
- I'm quitting.

1289
01:13:54,792 --> 01:13:56,500
- You're quitting?
- I'm not going to Turin.

1290
01:13:56,583 --> 01:13:59,143
I'm not doing the recital, audition,
and I'm not singing anymore.

1291
01:13:59,167 --> 01:14:00,875
Calm down. Calm down.

1292
01:14:00,958 --> 01:14:02,458
- Maybe...
- It's just not for me.

1293
01:14:02,542 --> 01:14:05,083
- I can't do it.
- It's normal to be nervous.

1294
01:14:05,167 --> 01:14:06,167
Completely normal.

1295
01:14:06,625 --> 01:14:07,917
Happens to every artist.

1296
01:14:08,000 --> 01:14:09,292
But I'm not an artist.

1297
01:14:09,375 --> 01:14:10,708
Of course you're not.

1298
01:14:11,333 --> 01:14:13,292
You're just someone who breeds donkeys.

1299
01:14:13,833 --> 01:14:15,500
Yep. Apparently.

1300
01:14:17,708 --> 01:14:18,708
Wait.

1301
01:14:18,792 --> 01:14:20,750
Why won't you tell me what happened?

1302
01:14:24,917 --> 01:14:26,917
[gentle acoustic music playing]

1303
01:14:51,208 --> 01:14:53,208
[airy vocalizations lilting]

1304
01:15:29,333 --> 01:15:30,958
Shall we go to the hair salon?

1305
01:15:41,708 --> 01:15:42,917
[shopkeeper bell rings]

1306
01:15:43,000 --> 01:15:44,125
But I like my hair straight.

1307
01:15:44,208 --> 01:15:45,848
Why not give it a try like that for once?

1308
01:15:45,917 --> 01:15:47,042
[music fades]

1309
01:15:47,125 --> 01:15:48,750
[sighs] alright, I'll try it.

1310
01:15:48,833 --> 01:15:51,250
But if I don't like it,
I'm washing it out at home.

1311
01:15:53,250 --> 01:15:54,250
Eletta.

1312
01:15:57,542 --> 01:15:58,875
Good morning, Professor.

1313
01:15:59,667 --> 01:16:01,958
- Hello.
- [Eletta] This is my mother.

1314
01:16:02,042 --> 01:16:04,125
Oh, I'm very pleased to meet you.

1315
01:16:04,208 --> 01:16:06,000
You know, you are very lucky.

1316
01:16:06,083 --> 01:16:09,208
Your daughter possesses
an extraordinary talent. A gift.

1317
01:16:09,292 --> 01:16:11,667
This is Giuliana, my teacher.

1318
01:16:15,250 --> 01:16:18,125
This woman is a nightmare!

1319
01:16:18,208 --> 01:16:20,125
Mama, she just wants to meet you.

1320
01:16:20,208 --> 01:16:21,417
I'd like to slap her!

1321
01:16:23,208 --> 01:16:24,667
Stay away from my daughter!

1322
01:16:24,750 --> 01:16:26,417
- What did I say?
- Stop it, Mama!

1323
01:16:26,500 --> 01:16:28,375
I wanted her to know
what I thought about you.

1324
01:16:28,458 --> 01:16:30,792
- Let's calm down.
- She's telling you what she thinks of me.

1325
01:16:30,875 --> 01:16:32,375
What she thinks of you?

1326
01:16:32,458 --> 01:16:36,667
You don't know my daughter at all.
I raised her.

1327
01:16:37,375 --> 01:16:39,833
She says she's the one who knows me best.

1328
01:16:41,833 --> 01:16:43,250
Because she's my mother.

1329
01:16:44,958 --> 01:16:47,583
It's okay.
My mother would say the same thing too.

1330
01:16:50,875 --> 01:16:53,792
All parents say that to each other.
It's not always the case.

1331
01:16:53,875 --> 01:16:56,042
What do you know?
You've never had children.

1332
01:16:56,125 --> 01:16:56,958
Mama!

1333
01:16:57,042 --> 01:16:58,250
What'd she say?

1334
01:16:58,833 --> 01:17:01,000
- Nothing.
- No, translate. What'd she say there?

1335
01:17:05,333 --> 01:17:08,083
She said, uh, that's 'cause
you don't have any children.

1336
01:17:08,167 --> 01:17:09,167
That's a fact!

1337
01:17:09,667 --> 01:17:12,292
Okay, I have no children.
Unfortunately, I have none.

1338
01:17:12,375 --> 01:17:14,917
That's true!
But I have a mother, and you're alike!

1339
01:17:15,417 --> 01:17:18,667
And she forced me to marry a man
who she said was perfect for me.

1340
01:17:18,750 --> 01:17:20,583
Except he cheated on me constantly.

1341
01:17:21,125 --> 01:17:23,708
So I know perfectly well
what it means to be manipulated.

1342
01:17:23,792 --> 01:17:25,042
Translate this, Eletta.

1343
01:17:26,708 --> 01:17:27,750
Eletta…

1344
01:17:30,958 --> 01:17:32,042
It's your life.

1345
01:17:35,708 --> 01:17:37,250
It's your life, sweetheart!

1346
01:17:38,625 --> 01:17:40,917
Don't let anyone decide
how you should live it.

1347
01:17:41,000 --> 01:17:43,583
Not me, not your parents. Understand?

1348
01:17:45,042 --> 01:17:47,542
Then she put her hands on her head
and messed up her hair.

1349
01:17:47,625 --> 01:17:48,625
- Liar.
- No.

1350
01:17:48,708 --> 01:17:50,875
- I would've paid to be there.
- I don't know.

1351
01:18:01,208 --> 01:18:02,208
He got out?

1352
01:18:04,792 --> 01:18:07,625
If he doesn't wanna go back in,
he'd better smarten up.

1353
01:18:08,458 --> 01:18:10,000
Maybe he'll sing again.

1354
01:18:11,000 --> 01:18:12,000
Hm!

1355
01:18:14,250 --> 01:18:15,458
[sighs softly]

1356
01:18:32,125 --> 01:18:34,417
[indistinct chatter]

1357
01:18:44,292 --> 01:18:47,833
If you're afraid of me, you can walk away.
You've turned and run before.

1358
01:18:47,917 --> 01:18:49,542
If you do, I'll understand.

1359
01:19:00,208 --> 01:19:02,583
You know the duet is quite challenging.

1360
01:19:05,167 --> 01:19:06,208
Can you do it?

1361
01:19:06,750 --> 01:19:08,417
Do you accept the challenge?

1362
01:19:22,833 --> 01:19:24,417
- Eletta.
- [indistinct chatter]

1363
01:19:25,917 --> 01:19:27,042
Are you nervous?

1364
01:19:27,125 --> 01:19:28,208
[breathes deeply]

1365
01:19:28,292 --> 01:19:29,500
Got another question?

1366
01:19:31,167 --> 01:19:32,375
Hey, it's gonna be fine.

1367
01:19:33,042 --> 01:19:34,250
How can you be so sure?

1368
01:19:34,333 --> 01:19:35,542
Because I showed up.

1369
01:19:37,292 --> 01:19:38,333
I like you.

1370
01:19:43,250 --> 01:19:44,333
I like you too.

1371
01:19:44,833 --> 01:19:49,458
<i>♪ I get knocked down but I get up again
You're never gonna keep me down ♪</i>

1372
01:19:49,542 --> 01:19:54,125
<i>♪ I get knocked down but I get up again
You're never gonna keep me down ♪</i>

1373
01:19:54,208 --> 01:19:58,667
<i>♪ I get knocked down but I get up again
You're never gonna keep me down ♪</i>

1374
01:19:58,750 --> 01:20:03,375
<i>♪ I get knocked down but I get up again
You're never gonna keep me down ♪</i>

1375
01:20:03,458 --> 01:20:05,000
<i>♪ I get knocked down! ♪</i>

1376
01:20:05,083 --> 01:20:06,167
[song ends]

1377
01:20:06,250 --> 01:20:08,250
[cheering]

1378
01:20:30,875 --> 01:20:33,875
["Non abbiam bisogno di parole"
playing on piano]

1379
01:20:43,042 --> 01:20:45,083
<i>♪ Now come here ♪</i>

1380
01:20:47,708 --> 01:20:51,458
<i>♪ And gently close your eyes ♪</i>

1381
01:20:54,125 --> 01:20:57,208
♪ <i>You'll see that</i>
<i>The sadness will go away </i> ♪

1382
01:20:58,333 --> 01:21:02,042
<i>♪ And the rest, who knows
It will come tomorrow ♪</i>

1383
01:21:07,917 --> 01:21:09,833
<i>♪ I want to be with you ♪</i>

1384
01:21:12,250 --> 01:21:15,833
<i>♪ Kiss your lips and tell you that ♪</i>

1385
01:21:18,583 --> 01:21:21,875
<i>♪ In a time when everything passes ♪</i>

1386
01:21:22,792 --> 01:21:24,958
[both] <i>♪ Where everything changes ♪</i>

1387
01:21:25,458 --> 01:21:27,708
♪ <i>We are still here </i> ♪

1388
01:21:29,125 --> 01:21:33,167
<i>♪ And we don't need words </i> ♪

1389
01:21:33,250 --> 01:21:35,792
[fading out] ♪ <i>To explain what is… ♪</i>

1390
01:21:35,875 --> 01:21:38,625
- [high-pitched tone]
- [soundscape fades]

1391
01:22:21,750 --> 01:22:26,583
[fading in] ♪ <i>I will follow your flight</i>
<i>Without ever interfering </i> ♪

1392
01:22:26,667 --> 01:22:28,583
[soundscape returns]

1393
01:22:28,667 --> 01:22:34,250
♪ <i>Because all I want is to be with you </i> ♪

1394
01:22:35,667 --> 01:22:38,042
<i>♪ Without chains </i> ♪

1395
01:22:38,125 --> 01:22:40,125
<i>♪ To be with… ♪</i>

1396
01:22:40,917 --> 01:22:42,208
<i>-You
-You</i>

1397
01:22:43,667 --> 01:22:44,667
[kisses]

1398
01:22:46,042 --> 01:22:49,042
[cheering and whistling]

1399
01:23:07,083 --> 01:23:08,583
You were incredible.

1400
01:23:23,292 --> 01:23:26,083
[screams] Oh, you were amazing!

1401
01:23:26,167 --> 01:23:27,917
- [laughs]
- Mwah!

1402
01:23:28,000 --> 01:23:30,125
- [chuckles] I'm so proud!
- [Eletta laughs]

1403
01:23:31,833 --> 01:23:33,917
Eletta. [Sighs deeply]

1404
01:23:34,417 --> 01:23:36,625
- Oh my God, you're amazing!
- [Eletta laughs]

1405
01:23:36,708 --> 01:23:39,833
[inhales deeply] I'm so proud.
Fantastic! It was magical!

1406
01:23:39,917 --> 01:23:41,667
Magical! [Shaky breaths]

1407
01:23:41,750 --> 01:23:42,750
Listen…

1408
01:23:43,458 --> 01:23:45,542
I never canceled tomorrow's audition.

1409
01:23:47,042 --> 01:23:50,292
You can still go and do it.
It's at ten in the morning in Turin…

1410
01:23:50,375 --> 01:23:52,417
- No, Professor.
- And I can take you.

1411
01:23:52,500 --> 01:23:54,125
- It's not possible.
- Uh…

1412
01:24:01,833 --> 01:24:03,042
Good evening.

1413
01:24:03,583 --> 01:24:04,667
[pants]

1414
01:24:04,750 --> 01:24:05,917
Good evening.

1415
01:24:06,000 --> 01:24:08,208
[pants] It's nice to meet you.

1416
01:24:08,792 --> 01:24:11,333
It is very nice to meet all of you.

1417
01:24:11,875 --> 01:24:12,875
Um…

1418
01:24:13,458 --> 01:24:17,625
And now that you know
the talent that is within your daughter,

1419
01:24:18,958 --> 01:24:22,833
I know you'll encourage her
to follow her own true path.

1420
01:24:22,917 --> 01:24:23,917
Right?

1421
01:24:25,833 --> 01:24:27,375
She learned our language.

1422
01:24:28,375 --> 01:24:31,125
Eletta… Eletta has a voice

1423
01:24:31,208 --> 01:24:33,125
that's extraordinary!

1424
01:24:33,208 --> 01:24:35,208
It's a wonderful voice. A gift.

1425
01:24:35,750 --> 01:24:38,583
Why would you silence it
instead of nurturing it?

1426
01:24:38,667 --> 01:24:41,500
Why would you stop her
instead of helping her? Why?

1427
01:24:42,042 --> 01:24:43,083
Why?

1428
01:24:43,167 --> 01:24:46,917
The show was fantastic.
Eletta moved everybody. My compliments.

1429
01:24:47,000 --> 01:24:51,250
My father… congratulates you
on the wonderful concert.

1430
01:24:53,375 --> 01:24:55,917
The staging was great,
and Eletta was well-dressed.

1431
01:24:57,542 --> 01:25:00,250
And my mother appreciated
the costumes and staging.

1432
01:25:00,333 --> 01:25:03,583
Eletta, you have to tell them your voice…
your voice is extraordinary.

1433
01:25:03,667 --> 01:25:06,542
- We're going. Uh, good… Goodbye.
- Tell her, though.

1434
01:25:06,625 --> 01:25:08,167
Eletta, tell her, please!

1435
01:25:11,125 --> 01:25:13,583
- [insects chirring]
- [donkey brays softly]

1436
01:25:13,667 --> 01:25:15,667
[footsteps approaching]

1437
01:25:30,958 --> 01:25:32,250
What is it?

1438
01:25:40,125 --> 01:25:42,917
It describes a love
that doesn't need to be spoken.

1439
01:25:47,792 --> 01:25:48,917
If you want.

1440
01:25:57,417 --> 01:25:59,333
[in Italian] <i>♪ Now come here ♪</i>

1441
01:26:02,167 --> 01:26:05,833
<i>♪ And gently close your eyes ♪</i>

1442
01:26:07,750 --> 01:26:11,125
<i>♪ You'll see that
The sadness will go away ♪</i>

1443
01:26:11,833 --> 01:26:15,500
<i>♪ And the rest, who knows
It will come tomorrow ♪</i>

1444
01:26:17,583 --> 01:26:19,750
<i>♪ I want to be with you ♪</i>

1445
01:26:21,625 --> 01:26:25,208
<i>♪ Kiss your lips and tell you that ♪</i>

1446
01:26:26,958 --> 01:26:30,542
<i>♪ In a time when everything passes ♪</i>

1447
01:26:31,333 --> 01:26:33,542
<i>♪ Where everything changes ♪</i>

1448
01:26:33,625 --> 01:26:35,750
<i>♪ We are still here ♪</i>

1449
01:26:38,417 --> 01:26:42,208
<i>♪ And we don't need words ♪</i>

1450
01:26:43,083 --> 01:26:49,125
<i>♪ To explain what is hidden
Deep in our hearts ♪</i>

1451
01:26:49,917 --> 01:26:55,750
<i>♪ But I will lift you up
Every time you fall ♪</i>

1452
01:26:55,833 --> 01:27:01,125
<i>♪ And I will pick up your flowers
That you'll lose on the street ♪</i>

1453
01:27:01,875 --> 01:27:06,792
<i>♪ And I will follow your flight
Without ever interfering ♪</i>

1454
01:27:08,500 --> 01:27:14,042
<i>♪ Because all I want is to be with you ♪</i>

1455
01:27:15,250 --> 01:27:18,458
<i>♪ Without chains ♪</i>

1456
01:27:18,542 --> 01:27:20,667
<i>♪ To be with you ♪</i>

1457
01:27:59,500 --> 01:28:00,583
What's the matter?

1458
01:28:00,667 --> 01:28:01,875
Get dressed.

1459
01:28:02,375 --> 01:28:03,708
Get dressed? Why?

1460
01:28:05,375 --> 01:28:06,375
Turin?

1461
01:28:10,958 --> 01:28:12,667
- [farts]
- Papa! [Laughs]

1462
01:28:13,792 --> 01:28:15,792
[line ringing]

1463
01:28:17,083 --> 01:28:19,083
[engine revving]

1464
01:28:21,667 --> 01:28:23,542
Professor. Professor!

1465
01:28:24,583 --> 01:28:25,500
Professor!

1466
01:28:25,583 --> 01:28:26,583
Holy fuck.

1467
01:28:27,000 --> 01:28:28,000
Miss!

1468
01:28:28,833 --> 01:28:31,125
Marco! What are you doing here so early?

1469
01:28:31,208 --> 01:28:32,833
Is that your car parked over there?

1470
01:28:32,917 --> 01:28:35,833
- It's the neighbors.' Why, what's up?
- Ask if we can borrow it.

1471
01:28:35,917 --> 01:28:37,500
You wanna borrow it to go where?

1472
01:28:37,583 --> 01:28:40,458
C'mon Papa. Please, go faster.
We're already running late!

1473
01:28:41,583 --> 01:28:44,463
- Haven't you read our messages?
- Marco, I didn't read them. I was asleep.

1474
01:28:44,542 --> 01:28:47,502
- Now if you don't tell me what's going on…
- Eletta's going to the audition!

1475
01:28:52,750 --> 01:28:55,042
Papa! Stop doing that! [Laughs]

1476
01:28:59,375 --> 01:29:01,375
Good morning. I'm here for the audition?

1477
01:29:01,458 --> 01:29:02,500
- Yes.
- Eletta Musso.

1478
01:29:02,583 --> 01:29:04,625
- Eletta Musso? But you're late.
- Sorry.

1479
01:29:04,708 --> 01:29:07,917
Alright, go up those stairs over there.
And your family should wait there.

1480
01:29:08,000 --> 01:29:09,375
- Thanks a lot.
- Thank you!

1481
01:29:10,375 --> 01:29:14,250
[woman singing in operatic soprano]

1482
01:29:14,333 --> 01:29:16,917
["Lascia ch'io pianga" playing on piano]

1483
01:29:41,375 --> 01:29:43,125
- Nicely done.
- [singer] Thank you.

1484
01:29:44,750 --> 01:29:45,833
Break a leg.

1485
01:29:46,583 --> 01:29:47,583
Thanks.

1486
01:29:55,333 --> 01:29:56,333
[breathes shakily]

1487
01:30:08,458 --> 01:30:10,542
Good morning. And your name is?

1488
01:30:10,625 --> 01:30:11,833
Eletta Musso.

1489
01:30:11,917 --> 01:30:14,226
One more minute of that music,
and I'd have slit my wrists.

1490
01:30:14,250 --> 01:30:16,091
One more minute of whining,
and I'd've let you.

1491
01:30:16,125 --> 01:30:17,417
What song have you chosen?

